WEBVTT

00:00.758 --> 00:02.119
Previously on <i>Smash</i>.

00:02.982 --> 00:06.017
You want to direct this show so much?...
Now's your chance. I quit.

00:06.035 --> 00:08.369
I'm not your Marilyn.
She is.

00:08.404 --> 00:11.456
- Ivy, darling!
- Mom?

00:11.490 --> 00:13.691
So I cast her mother.
Is that really so unforgivable?

00:13.709 --> 00:17.361
I have let <i>Bombshell</i> go,
just not its leading lady.

00:17.379 --> 00:19.130
I'll let you know
if I need you again.

00:19.164 --> 00:21.833
♪ Tell me what I do

00:21.867 --> 00:24.085
New musicals
take years to develop.

00:24.136 --> 00:25.470
Derek Wills
directing our show.

00:25.504 --> 00:27.305
My show
needs your help.

00:27.339 --> 00:29.540
- You said you didn't need me.
- So you ran off to help Derek?

00:29.558 --> 00:31.426
I'm moving <i>Hit List</i>
<i>to Broadway.</i>

00:31.477 --> 00:33.845
This way, I can take
that Tony away from you.

00:33.879 --> 00:35.212
♪ When I heard your voice

00:35.230 --> 00:37.515
I mean, how much do you
really know about this guy?

00:37.549 --> 00:38.850
The <i>New York Times</i> said

00:38.884 --> 00:40.652
that Jimmy Collins
isn't even his real name.

00:40.686 --> 00:42.654
[Cheering]
All this is 'cause of you.

00:42.688 --> 00:44.155
[Tires screeching]

00:44.189 --> 00:46.240
- He's dead because of me.
- It was an accident.

00:46.275 --> 00:49.243
- To Kyle.
- All: To Kyle.

00:49.278 --> 00:50.578
I need the show
to be perfect.

00:50.612 --> 00:53.081
- Now he wants a Tony.
- Not for me, for Kyle.

00:53.115 --> 00:56.084
- How is it going with you guys?
- He barely talks to me.

00:56.118 --> 00:57.919
- Give her tomorrow night off.
- And put Daisy in?

00:57.953 --> 00:59.070
She's one
of the six dancers

00:59.088 --> 01:00.922
who accused Derek
of sexual harassment.

01:00.956 --> 01:02.406
♪ I'm not sorry, sorry

01:02.424 --> 01:04.075
I told her
if we went to Broadway,

01:04.093 --> 01:06.260
she could be an understudy
if she really wanted it,

01:06.295 --> 01:08.046
and she showed me
that she did.

01:08.080 --> 01:09.714
Derek just fired me.
He fired you too.

01:09.748 --> 01:11.015
Is it because you stopped
sleeping with him?

01:11.050 --> 01:12.216
Excuse me?

01:12.250 --> 01:13.968
The only thing better
than getting a Tony

01:14.019 --> 01:15.920
will be beating you to get it.

01:15.938 --> 01:17.939
Ivy Lynn, you're pregnant.

01:17.973 --> 01:19.273
♪ I'm not sorry

01:19.343 --> 01:23.016
Sync and corrected by dr.jackson
for www.addic7ed.com

01:23.076 --> 01:24.261
[ <i>Feelin' alright</i> playing]

01:24.279 --> 01:30.284
♪

01:32.621 --> 01:38.242
♪ Seems I got to have
a change of scene ♪

01:38.276 --> 01:43.297
♪ every night I have
the strangest dreams ♪

01:43.332 --> 01:49.053
♪ imprisoned by the way
it could have been and ♪

01:49.088 --> 01:54.458
♪ left here on my own
or so it seems ♪

01:54.476 --> 02:00.131
♪ I got to leave
before I start to scream ♪

02:00.149 --> 02:04.402
♪ but someone locked the door
and took the key ♪

02:04.436 --> 02:08.906
♪ you feelin' all right
♪ oh, oh

02:08.941 --> 02:12.326
♪ I'm not feelin'
too good myself ♪

02:12.361 --> 02:14.028
♪ oh, oh

02:14.079 --> 02:17.782
♪ yes, sir,
you feelin' all right ♪

02:17.816 --> 02:19.584
♪ oh, oh

02:19.618 --> 02:22.987
♪ I'm not feelin'
that good myself ♪

02:23.005 --> 02:24.655
♪ oh, oh

02:24.673 --> 02:29.343
♪

02:29.378 --> 02:31.662
Eileen, check it out.

02:31.680 --> 02:34.832
Ten outer critics circle
nominations!

02:34.850 --> 02:38.936
<i>Hit List</i> got 11.

02:38.971 --> 02:40.021
[Knocking at door]

02:40.055 --> 02:42.723
Ivy, it's time
for the curtain call.

02:42.775 --> 02:44.459
I'll be right out.

02:44.493 --> 02:49.513
♪ I must keep trying,
you're feelin' all right ♪

02:49.531 --> 02:51.532
♪ oh, oh

02:51.567 --> 02:54.185
♪ I'm not feelin'
too good myself ♪

02:54.203 --> 02:56.704
[Cheers and applause]
♪ oh, oh

02:56.738 --> 03:00.291
♪ oh, no
you're feelin' all right ♪

03:00.325 --> 03:02.359
♪ oh, oh

03:02.377 --> 03:04.528
♪ I'm not feelin' too good

03:04.546 --> 03:07.715
[cheers and applause]
Daisy! Daisy!

03:07.749 --> 03:10.751
[Laughter]
She's sensational, Derek.

03:10.803 --> 03:12.670
I don't know
how you find them.

03:12.704 --> 03:16.257
Yeah, just really lucky,
I guess.

03:19.595 --> 03:21.729
The outer critics circle
are a bunch of sadists.

03:21.763 --> 03:23.214
They don't call you
to tell you if you've won.

03:23.232 --> 03:25.066
You have to keep refreshing
their website to find out.

03:25.100 --> 03:27.685
Yeah, well, checking
your phone every 15 seconds

03:27.719 --> 03:29.270
isn't gonna help.
[Scoffs]

03:29.321 --> 03:31.489
Without this win, I might not
get a Tony nomination.

03:31.523 --> 03:32.607
Without a Tony nomination,

03:32.658 --> 03:34.058
I might never
get to direct again,

03:34.076 --> 03:35.526
and if I don't get to direct
again, then the whole...

03:35.560 --> 03:38.346
Tom, we have
a real chance here.

03:38.380 --> 03:40.264
Are you ready
to go back in?

03:40.299 --> 03:41.420
There's Tony voters
in there.

03:41.433 --> 03:43.467
They need to see
we support the competition.

03:43.501 --> 03:46.503
All three acts of it.
All righty.

03:49.141 --> 03:52.393
They who desire me to be dumb
on the subject of slavery...

03:52.444 --> 03:54.896
- [Sighs]
- Unless I will open my mouth

03:54.947 --> 03:59.450
in its defense, ask me to give
the lie to my professions,

03:59.484 --> 04:03.237
degrade my memory,
and disdain my soul.

04:03.288 --> 04:06.657
I will not be a liar,
a poltroon, or a hypocrite

04:06.691 --> 04:08.125
[whispering]
Sorry.

04:08.160 --> 04:11.445
To accommodate any party,
to gratify any sect,

04:11.480 --> 04:14.698
to escape any odium
or peril,

04:14.716 --> 04:19.503
to save any interest,
to preserve any institution,

04:19.536 --> 04:22.740
or to promote any object.

04:22.758 --> 04:24.542
[Whispering]
Wh... what are you doing?

04:24.576 --> 04:25.910
[Whispering]
My phone, I dropped it.

04:25.944 --> 04:28.179
Excuse me.
I'm sorry.

04:28.213 --> 04:30.965
I just... [grunts]

04:33.135 --> 04:34.135
[Gasps]

04:34.152 --> 04:35.720
Oh, my God, I won.
[Laughs]

04:35.754 --> 04:37.722
Are you kidding me?

04:37.756 --> 04:40.975
Haven't you ever been
to a theater before?

04:41.026 --> 04:45.363
Not only have I been there,
I just won a major award for it:

04:45.397 --> 04:46.731
Best director.

04:48.884 --> 04:50.952
Patrick Dillon?

04:54.256 --> 04:57.742
It's okay, guys, you can talk
about it, it's only one award.

04:57.776 --> 05:00.044
- Karen shouldn't have won.
- [Sighs]

05:00.078 --> 05:02.330
Guess all that trash talking
she did about me paid off.

05:02.381 --> 05:06.300
[Chuckles] Yeah, but hey,
awards are not important, right?

05:06.335 --> 05:07.969
You're only saying that
because you just won one,

05:08.003 --> 05:10.621
and for a tiny role.

05:10.639 --> 05:12.673
- Ouch.
- I'm... I'm so sorry.

05:12.724 --> 05:14.091
- Oh, no, it's...
- I don't know

05:14.125 --> 05:15.343
what's gotten into me.

05:15.394 --> 05:16.644
I haven't
been feeling well lately.

05:16.678 --> 05:18.062
You just need some food.

05:18.096 --> 05:20.982
No, uh, why don't you guys
go ahead without me.

05:21.016 --> 05:25.302
- I'ml'm not hungry, I'm sorry.
- No...

05:25.320 --> 05:27.271
She's been like this
all week.

05:27.305 --> 05:28.990
She almost missed
the curtain call today.

05:29.024 --> 05:30.942
She fell asleep
in her dressing room

05:30.976 --> 05:32.443
during intermission
last night.

05:32.477 --> 05:35.145
Seems like old times?

05:35.163 --> 05:37.114
Hey, you guys,
she wouldn't relapse

05:37.148 --> 05:38.783
just 'cause of everything
that's going on now.

05:38.817 --> 05:41.285
I don't know.
She <i>Black-Swaned</i> once before,

05:41.319 --> 05:45.322
and that was only Boston.
This is Broadway.

05:47.426 --> 05:49.877
Congratulations, Tom.
That was a good win.

05:49.928 --> 05:54.181
Well, I tied with Derek
for <i>hit lis</i> but still.

05:54.216 --> 05:57.268
There's hope for us yet.

05:57.302 --> 05:59.687
- Did you see who that was?
- Of course.

05:59.721 --> 06:01.722
I've had a crush on him
for forever.

06:01.773 --> 06:04.475
Think the rumors are true?
No one knows,

06:04.509 --> 06:05.843
but if you ask me,
he's the reason

06:05.861 --> 06:09.563
they came up with the term
"glass closet."

06:09.614 --> 06:11.315
I love his movies.

06:11.349 --> 06:13.034
His <i>Long day's journey</i>
<i>Into night</i> last season,

06:13.068 --> 06:14.368
not so much.

06:14.403 --> 06:15.720
Well,
he won a Tony for it,

06:15.754 --> 06:17.688
so he's on the nominating
committee this year.

06:17.706 --> 06:21.158
Not a good person to piss off.
You're joking, right?

06:21.192 --> 06:25.463
Uh oh.<i>Bombshell</i>
<i>only got two awards.</i>

06:25.497 --> 06:28.165
You for director
and Julia for book.

06:28.199 --> 06:31.002
<i>Hit List</i> took the rest.

06:31.036 --> 06:34.038
You better hope
he doesn't hold a grudge.

06:41.229 --> 06:42.313
Only winners get to go

06:42.347 --> 06:43.847
to the outer critics circle
luncheon,

06:43.865 --> 06:46.233
but since we practically
swept the awards,

06:46.284 --> 06:48.152
we have the whole table.

06:48.186 --> 06:49.487
What's this?

06:49.521 --> 06:51.322
Tony nominations.
They're announced next Tuesday.

06:51.356 --> 06:53.391
These are mock-ups
from what we're expecting.

06:53.425 --> 06:54.992
You sure Daisy's photo's
big enough?

06:55.026 --> 06:58.212
It's sufficient, yes.

06:58.246 --> 07:00.697
Why isn't Kyle on here
for best book?

07:00.716 --> 07:04.701
It's not a nomination
we're expecting.

07:04.720 --> 07:07.088
He did a great job,

07:07.139 --> 07:09.256
but Julia Houston won the OCC.

07:09.307 --> 07:11.375
Everybody knows
she's a lock for the Tony.

07:11.393 --> 07:14.145
Our show is basically
sung through.

07:14.179 --> 07:16.814
So were <i>rent</i> and
<i>passing strange</i> and they won.

07:16.848 --> 07:19.216
[Sighs]
Look...

07:19.234 --> 07:22.219
He's just not getting
any traction out there.

07:22.237 --> 07:26.223
But not to worry... we are
right in line for best musical.

07:26.241 --> 07:27.274
[Knocking at door]

07:27.325 --> 07:29.493
- Yeah?
- This just came for you.

07:29.528 --> 07:30.911
Thanks.

07:30.946 --> 07:32.997
Okay, okay, forget it.

07:33.031 --> 07:34.782
I'll... I'll campaign
for him myself.

07:34.833 --> 07:36.751
I'll take out an ad.
We got a couple days left.

07:36.785 --> 07:39.453
Oh, you two are worrying
about the wrong thing.

07:39.504 --> 07:41.705
This could ruin us.
What? What is it?

07:41.739 --> 07:45.793
It's from
Ana Vargas's lawyer.

07:45.844 --> 07:48.429
She's filing
a wrongful termination suit

07:48.463 --> 07:51.932
against Derek Wills
and Jerry Rand productions.

07:51.967 --> 07:53.467
What? Why?

07:53.518 --> 07:57.354
"Derek promised the diva role
to Daisy Parker

07:57.389 --> 08:00.491
if she slept with him."

08:00.525 --> 08:03.911
Is that true?

08:07.282 --> 08:10.434
You knew about this.

08:10.452 --> 08:12.069
Wow,
thanks for telling me.

08:12.103 --> 08:13.654
- Jimmy...
- Great.

08:13.705 --> 08:16.373
Wait, I...
Hold on a second.

08:19.327 --> 08:23.214
If this girl blows up my show
during nomination week,

08:23.248 --> 08:25.516
Derek...
I'll take care of it.

08:27.252 --> 08:29.653
You better.

08:29.688 --> 08:33.340
[Door opening and closing]

08:33.375 --> 08:35.342
Karen.

08:35.393 --> 08:37.344
You need to tell Ana
to back off.

08:37.395 --> 08:39.429
- No, I don't.
- Well, at least tell her

08:39.464 --> 08:41.899
that she's gonna destroy
her own career as well as mine

08:41.933 --> 08:43.567
if she doesn't stop this.
Well, maybe some things

08:43.602 --> 08:44.602
are more important
than a career,

08:44.636 --> 08:47.054
- like self-respect.
- Yeah, maybe.

08:47.088 --> 08:50.307
Look,
Ana is a talented girl.

08:50.342 --> 08:52.843
If she's patient,
things will pick up for her.

08:52.878 --> 08:57.948
It's too late, Derek.
It's all coming down on you now.

09:00.068 --> 09:04.538
[Phone buzzing]

09:04.589 --> 09:05.623
Yeah.

09:05.657 --> 09:07.691
Derek, I was hoping
we could meet.

09:07.726 --> 09:09.493
I-I left you a few messages,
but...

09:09.511 --> 09:10.878
Look, Ivy, not now.

09:10.929 --> 09:15.449
- I need to talk to you about...
- Ivy, not now, okay?

09:15.484 --> 09:18.502
I'm sorry.

09:19.421 --> 09:22.723
[Door opens and closes]

09:22.774 --> 09:25.609
I know it's a big decision,
but meanwhile,

09:25.644 --> 09:28.812
I want to keep taking
your prenatals, just to be safe.

09:28.846 --> 09:30.781
Thanks, Dr. Holland.

09:30.815 --> 09:33.817
You'll let me know
what you decide?

09:38.773 --> 09:39.773
Hit it.

09:39.791 --> 09:41.175
[Upbeat jazz music]

09:41.209 --> 09:42.993
♪ One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight ♪

09:43.027 --> 09:44.662
♪ one, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight ♪

09:44.696 --> 09:46.797
♪ one, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight ♪

09:46.831 --> 09:48.582
♪ one, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight ♪

09:48.633 --> 09:50.484
♪ one, two, three, four,
five, six ♪

09:50.519 --> 09:52.336
♪ one, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight ♪

09:52.370 --> 09:54.171
♪ one, two, three, four,
five, six ♪

09:54.205 --> 09:55.639
♪ one, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight ♪

09:55.674 --> 09:57.808
♪ five, six, seven, eight!

09:59.990 --> 10:02.646
I'm sorry to ****

10:03.290 --> 10:05.824
My divorce was a horror show.

10:05.842 --> 10:08.994
If you want my lawyer,
I'll give her your number.

10:09.012 --> 10:10.496
She's a pit bull.

10:10.514 --> 10:14.850
Ugh, Eileen, we have lost
so much for this show.

10:14.885 --> 10:16.702
Do you ever wonder
if it's worth it?

10:16.737 --> 10:19.138
Every day.

10:19.172 --> 10:22.808
I lost my house,
I lost my money,

10:22.843 --> 10:24.794
I lost Nick.

10:24.828 --> 10:26.345
[Door opens]

10:26.363 --> 10:27.630
Hello.

10:27.664 --> 10:30.516
I thought
you'd like to know,

10:30.534 --> 10:33.569
I fixed the situation
with Patrick Dillon.

10:33.620 --> 10:35.721
[Clears throat]
I found out where he lives

10:35.756 --> 10:38.708
and sent over
a very nice bottle of wine

10:38.742 --> 10:40.526
and a lovely
little apology note.

10:40.560 --> 10:43.479
Oh, Tom.
You have to cancel that order.

10:43.513 --> 10:44.747
What are you talking
about?

10:44.798 --> 10:46.799
There are strict rules
about giving gifts

10:46.833 --> 10:49.118
to members
of the nominating committee.

10:49.152 --> 10:52.471
Thisthis wasn't a gift.
It was a bottle of wine,

10:52.506 --> 10:55.174
a petite syrah, at that.
In some circles,

10:55.208 --> 10:58.010
they don't consider that
a gift at all.

10:58.045 --> 10:59.879
Let's hope
he sees it that way.

10:59.913 --> 11:01.998
He could use it to sanction you
or, worse still,

11:02.032 --> 11:06.185
disqualify you
from the awards.

11:06.219 --> 11:10.806
Well, um, maybe I can try
and cancel the order.

11:10.841 --> 11:13.859
Yes, I hope
it's not too late.

11:19.683 --> 11:21.033
[Door thuds]
Ah.

11:23.770 --> 11:25.838
[Sighs]

11:29.426 --> 11:32.328
You need
to leave the show.

11:32.362 --> 11:35.181
Health issue, family emergency,
I don't care what.

11:35.215 --> 11:37.416
Bow out now,
Ana gets her role back,

11:37.451 --> 11:39.035
and this doesn't have to get
any uglier.

11:39.069 --> 11:40.586
[Chuckles]

11:40.604 --> 11:43.222
Oh. Oh, you feel good
about yourself?

11:43.256 --> 11:45.057
About how you got
this job?

11:45.091 --> 11:47.476
- How did you get this job?
- I worked my ass off.

11:47.527 --> 11:49.228
I found the composer,
and I created the role,

11:49.262 --> 11:50.362
and I didn't sleep
with the director

11:50.397 --> 11:51.480
and then blackmail him.

11:51.531 --> 11:53.251
No, you did everything
but sleep with him.

11:53.266 --> 11:56.769
You played the game too.
Look, Karen,

11:56.787 --> 12:00.939
unlike you, I have been trying
to get here for ten years.

12:00.957 --> 12:03.793
Ten years of lost roles,
endless showcases,

12:03.827 --> 12:06.629
teaching pilates,
all the while knowing

12:06.663 --> 12:10.082
I was just as good if not better
than everyone around me.

12:10.117 --> 12:14.370
After two years of that,
let alone ten, you stop caring

12:14.404 --> 12:16.505
about being a good person.
You do what it takes.

12:16.556 --> 12:19.742
You know who else
has been here a long time,

12:19.776 --> 12:22.311
paying her dues?
Ana.

12:22.345 --> 12:24.063
And now
she's completely screwed.

12:24.097 --> 12:25.314
She can't even get
a real audition.

12:25.348 --> 12:27.183
I'm sorry about that.

12:27.217 --> 12:29.902
I am, but that's not my fault,
it's Derek's.

12:29.936 --> 12:31.353
All I did was say yes.

12:31.404 --> 12:32.521
And that was your choice.

12:32.572 --> 12:35.591
You can choose another one,
the right one.

12:35.625 --> 12:40.913
I won an award today.
I'm not leaving.

12:45.268 --> 12:48.254
Yeah.
[Coughs]

12:48.288 --> 12:51.340
Uh, k-Karen totally deserved
her win today.

12:51.374 --> 12:53.676
We're... we're very lucky
to have her.

12:53.710 --> 12:56.212
Leaving <i>Bombshell</i>
<i>and taking a risk with your show</i>

12:56.263 --> 12:57.379
was a good move,
it seems.

12:57.430 --> 12:59.498
Yeah.
Yeah, I'd say so.

12:59.516 --> 13:02.968
I mean, with <i>Bombshell,</i>
<i>she was just imitating an icon,</i>

13:03.002 --> 13:06.305
and here she actually, you know,
created a real character.

13:06.339 --> 13:08.190
"Imitating an icon."

13:08.225 --> 13:10.008
Is that what you think
Ivy Lynn is doing?

13:10.026 --> 13:11.861
Well, I mean,
I'm just saying

13:11.895 --> 13:13.863
that a lot of actresses
have played Marilyn,

13:13.897 --> 13:15.397
and Karen
is the first Amanda.

13:15.448 --> 13:17.128
Hey, can we get back
to talking about Kyle?

13:17.150 --> 13:19.568
Karen! We were just
talking about you.

13:19.619 --> 13:20.736
Hey, hi.

13:20.787 --> 13:23.989
Yeah, and Kyle...
Kyle, uh... [laughs]

13:24.023 --> 13:26.358
I asked you to do this interview
so that people would know

13:26.376 --> 13:27.793
that <i>Hit List</i> wouldn't exist
without him.

13:27.828 --> 13:32.081
Oh, what about Julia Houston?
How does she fit in all this?

13:32.132 --> 13:33.749
I'm so... I'm sorry,
what do you mean?

13:33.783 --> 13:36.552
There's a lot of talk about
how close she and Kyle were.

13:36.586 --> 13:40.139
People are assuming she did
a lot of work on this show.

13:40.173 --> 13:42.091
- Excuse me?
- Oh, let me clear this up,

13:42.142 --> 13:43.208
if that's okay.

13:43.226 --> 13:45.261
<i>Hit List</i>
is Kyle's vision.

13:45.312 --> 13:48.063
It all started with him.

13:48.098 --> 13:51.650
It's the statement
he left to the world.

13:51.685 --> 13:53.686
And Julia's a friend of mine,
she's a friend to our show,

13:53.720 --> 13:56.405
we love her,
but whatever you're hearing,

13:56.439 --> 13:57.990
it just... it isn't true.

13:58.024 --> 14:00.776
Off the record,
someone should tell her

14:00.827 --> 14:03.195
to stop speaking about Kyle
so much.

14:03.229 --> 14:04.509
It's giving
the wrong impression.

14:04.531 --> 14:06.615
- Oh, we will. We...
- Thanks for your time.

14:06.666 --> 14:09.668
- Thanks.
- Certainly will.

14:11.705 --> 14:14.006
I cannot believe t
she is sabotaging our show.

14:14.040 --> 14:16.926
Jimmy, she's not.
You're so wound up.

14:16.960 --> 14:18.711
She loved Kyle, that's why
she's talking about him.

14:18.745 --> 14:21.213
Besides, she had
her own dramaturge on <i>Bombshell,</i>

14:21.248 --> 14:23.215
this guy Peter Gilman.

14:23.249 --> 14:25.250
She's sensitive
to keeping a script doctor

14:25.268 --> 14:26.635
behind the scenes.

14:26.686 --> 14:29.221
Hmm.

14:31.608 --> 14:33.609
Hello.

14:35.000 --> 14:41.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

14:46.206 --> 14:48.440
What are you doing?

14:50.210 --> 14:52.544
That's a delivery
for Mr. Dillon.

14:52.579 --> 14:55.297
Yes, I'm the one
who sent it.

14:55.332 --> 14:58.918
That's... that's my name
on the card.

14:58.952 --> 15:01.320
There's been a mistake.
I need to take it back.

15:01.354 --> 15:03.055
He's on his way down
right now to get it.

15:03.089 --> 15:05.007
You can explain it to him
yourself.

15:05.058 --> 15:07.843
That won't be necessary.

15:07.894 --> 15:09.645
- Do I need to call the police?
- Oh. No.

15:09.679 --> 15:10.813
[Paper tears]

15:10.847 --> 15:13.098
Chintzy.
Hey, man, what's going on?

15:13.132 --> 15:15.818
It's nothing.

15:15.852 --> 15:18.070
Hi again. Um,

15:18.104 --> 15:21.740
I got you this bottle of wine
to apologize...

15:21.775 --> 15:24.026
[Whispering] If I could just...
Thank you.

15:24.077 --> 15:25.995
Not knowing
that was against the rules.

15:26.029 --> 15:27.579
So I was taking it back,

15:27.614 --> 15:30.366
and I was hoping that you
wouldn't even know about it.

15:30.417 --> 15:33.002
A petite syrah,
that's your apology?

15:33.036 --> 15:37.039
[Chuckles]
Um...

15:40.794 --> 15:42.344
What are you doing?

15:42.379 --> 15:44.930
Just let me take it back, and
we'll forget the whole thing.

15:44.965 --> 15:46.765
- No, let go.
- No.

15:46.800 --> 15:48.017
- You're...
- This is insane.

15:48.051 --> 15:49.334
Please let go of the bottle.
Please let go of...

15:49.352 --> 15:50.853
- [Grunts] You... just...
- You're very strong.

15:50.887 --> 15:53.055
- Stop it! I know I'm strong.
- Please let go of the bottle!

15:53.106 --> 15:55.975
You don't understand!
Gimme it!

15:56.009 --> 16:00.095
Oh... my... God.

16:00.130 --> 16:03.148
Please tell me
those are J. crew.

16:04.818 --> 16:06.351
I don't know
what's happened to me.

16:06.369 --> 16:10.205
I'm usually
so calm and collected.

16:10.240 --> 16:12.291
I... send me... send me
the dry cleaning bill.

16:12.325 --> 16:13.325
- I'll pay for it.
- Tom!

16:13.326 --> 16:14.743
No, please. Please.

16:14.794 --> 16:19.465
Tom, you've done enough.
Now, please, leave me alone.

16:19.499 --> 16:21.967
Enjoy your outer critics
circle award,

16:22.002 --> 16:25.137
in case it's the only one
you get.

16:27.540 --> 16:30.542
[Sighs]

16:36.766 --> 16:38.767
You got it?

16:40.487 --> 16:42.154
Okay, so why are you
really here?

16:42.188 --> 16:44.490
My show lets out before yours,
and I wanted to see my friend.

16:44.524 --> 16:45.557
Is there anything wrong
with that?

16:45.575 --> 16:46.575
- Hmm.
- Ivy!

16:46.576 --> 16:47.693
[Cheering]
Ivy, over here!

16:47.727 --> 16:49.161
Hi.
[Laughs]

16:49.195 --> 16:51.280
I can't believe <i>Hit List</i>
won all those awards.

16:51.331 --> 16:55.117
Your show
is so much better.

16:55.168 --> 16:56.618
- Sorry. [Laughs]
- It's okay.

16:56.669 --> 16:58.120
[Laughter]
Thank you.

16:58.171 --> 16:59.401
Seriously, Sam, what's up?

16:59.427 --> 17:02.240
Listen, if you're having problems,
you need to talk to me.

17:02.258 --> 17:03.342
Problems?
What problems?

17:03.376 --> 17:05.077
Karen should not have
beaten you.

17:05.095 --> 17:06.962
Oh, <i>Hit List</i>
is a wonderful show,

17:07.012 --> 17:08.763
and Karen's wonderful
in it.

17:08.798 --> 17:09.848
[Laughter]
Hi.

17:09.883 --> 17:11.884
Everybody is worried
about you.

17:11.917 --> 17:14.053
Worried about me, why?

17:14.087 --> 17:15.554
Did you hear
what Karen and Jimmy

17:15.588 --> 17:17.890
- said about you in <i>The Voice?</i>
- No, what did they say?

17:17.924 --> 17:19.525
- She doesn't need to hear that.
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

17:19.559 --> 17:22.394
Your performance is the furthest
thing from an imitation.

17:22.428 --> 17:24.646
An imitation?
Is that what Karen said?

17:24.696 --> 17:26.565
Yeah, and that <i>Bombshell</i>
isn't original.

17:26.598 --> 17:29.151
Listen, the only reason
<i>Hit List</i> even made it

17:29.202 --> 17:31.103
to Broadway is because
Kyle Bishop died. [Laughs]

17:31.121 --> 17:33.455
All: [Gasp]
- Ivy.

17:33.490 --> 17:36.241
Uh ohh.

17:40.657 --> 17:47.426
♪ Are you really here,
or am I dreaming? ♪

17:47.675 --> 17:52.679
♪ I can't tell dreams
from truth ♪

17:52.713 --> 17:55.882
♪ for it's been so long

17:55.933 --> 17:59.669
♪ since I have seen you

17:59.687 --> 18:05.225
♪ I can hardly remember
your face anymore ♪

18:05.276 --> 18:11.314
♪ when I get really lonely

18:11.348 --> 18:16.653
♪ and the distance causes
only silence ♪

18:16.687 --> 18:20.356
♪ then I think

18:20.374 --> 18:23.910
♪ of you smiling

18:23.961 --> 18:26.863
♪ with pride in your eyes

18:26.881 --> 18:30.383
♪ a lover that sighs

18:30.418 --> 18:36.389
♪ if you want me

18:36.424 --> 18:42.395
♪ satisfy me

18:42.430 --> 18:48.401
♪ if you want me

18:48.436 --> 18:54.407
♪ satisfy me

18:54.442 --> 18:57.994
[song ends]

18:58.029 --> 19:00.563
- That was beautiful, Ana.
- Thank you.

19:00.581 --> 19:02.282
Thank you
for coming in so fast.

19:02.333 --> 19:04.918
Oh, you have no idea how much
I needed this call today.

19:04.952 --> 19:05.952
[Laughs]

19:06.003 --> 19:08.071
What's your life like
right now?

19:08.089 --> 19:09.472
Can you go on tour?

19:09.507 --> 19:12.125
I am wide open.
And I love <i>once.</i>

19:12.176 --> 19:13.960
I'm so honored
to be considered.

19:14.011 --> 19:16.913
You were even better
than Derek said you were.

19:16.931 --> 19:19.299
Derek Wills?

19:19.350 --> 19:23.353
He recommended you,
pushed pretty hard too.

19:24.889 --> 19:28.141
This is why...

19:28.192 --> 19:29.593
You've been acting so nuts.

19:29.627 --> 19:32.729
You're pregnant.

19:32.763 --> 19:38.235
So are we sure
that it's Derek's?

19:38.269 --> 19:42.038
Unfortunately, I narrowed
it down from a list of one.

19:42.073 --> 19:44.774
When are you telling him?

19:47.962 --> 19:51.748
You're not telling him.

19:51.782 --> 19:55.635
We're not even together.

19:55.670 --> 19:57.888
We didn't plan it, we didn't
even want it to happen.

19:57.922 --> 20:01.174
Hey, Ivy, he has a right
to know he's a father.

20:01.225 --> 20:04.244
Right now,
he's just a guy I slept with.

20:04.278 --> 20:07.397
I'll decide if he's going
to be the father.

20:10.067 --> 20:14.304
Sam, do you think
I could be a good mom?

20:16.123 --> 20:21.027
You are a great friend,
and it usually translates.

20:23.147 --> 20:26.533
I'm just such a mess
right now.

20:26.584 --> 20:29.035
And of course,
right when my career takes off,

20:29.086 --> 20:32.756
this has to happen.
[Sighs]

20:32.790 --> 20:37.627
Classic Ivy.
Absolutely worst timing ever.

20:37.661 --> 20:42.132
Listen, Ivy, you have
got to discuss this with Derek,

20:42.166 --> 20:47.921
no matter what you decide to do.
I know he's not always easy,

20:47.955 --> 20:50.974
but he cares about you.

20:54.278 --> 20:56.396
Why is Ivy here?

20:56.447 --> 20:58.615
She's the last person
I wanted to see today.

20:58.649 --> 21:01.651
I know. Thank you.

21:03.871 --> 21:07.624
- What can I get you?
- Just water.

21:09.126 --> 21:11.461
I feel like I'm going to be
stoned to death.

21:11.495 --> 21:13.997
I know I shouldn't
say this,

21:14.031 --> 21:17.033
but I thought <i>Hit List</i>
<i>was way overrated too.</i>

21:17.051 --> 21:20.553
I mean, you've seen
the comments online.

21:20.588 --> 21:23.590
We're not the only ones.

21:23.641 --> 21:25.725
Hey. What's going on?

21:25.760 --> 21:28.728
Have you seen this?

21:28.763 --> 21:32.983
Ah, if it isn't
my two favorite P.R. disasters.

21:33.017 --> 21:34.601
What are you gonna do
for an encore today,

21:34.652 --> 21:36.236
burn down table 46?

21:36.270 --> 21:39.739
I guess I've created
a backlash against <i>Hit List.</i>

21:39.774 --> 21:41.191
Should I just leave?

21:41.225 --> 21:42.725
No, you have to show
your face.

21:42.743 --> 21:46.396
You're here to support Julia,
Tom, and the show.

21:46.414 --> 21:49.399
- Patrick Dillon's here.
- Are we not good there?

21:49.417 --> 21:51.951
You should know
that our encounter with the wine

21:52.003 --> 21:53.503
did not go well.

21:53.537 --> 21:56.072
Stay away from him, Tom.
You've done enough damage.

21:56.090 --> 22:00.343
Eileen. Thought
you'd be wearing black today.

22:00.378 --> 22:04.631
No, Jerry, I'm saving it
for your funeral.

22:04.682 --> 22:08.301
- Hey.
- Hey.

22:08.352 --> 22:10.770
You're looking
uncommonly radiant.

22:10.805 --> 22:12.555
[Chuckles]

22:12.589 --> 22:14.090
Did you get your hair done,
or something?

22:14.108 --> 22:16.476
Don't try to make me
feel better, Derek.

22:16.527 --> 22:20.930
I know everybody hates me.
Well, I don't.

22:20.948 --> 22:23.033
Look, sorry, I was
in the middle of something

22:23.067 --> 22:26.052
when you called yesterday.
What did you want to say?

22:28.773 --> 22:30.657
Congratulations.

22:30.708 --> 22:35.278
Really?
Sounded more urgent than that.

22:37.648 --> 22:41.451
Can we meet up here tonight
after my show?

22:41.469 --> 22:44.337
I just kind of want to talk.

22:47.291 --> 22:50.260
I would love that.

22:50.294 --> 22:53.263
[Piano playing]

22:53.297 --> 22:57.567
♪

22:57.601 --> 23:00.236
[Song ends]

23:00.271 --> 23:03.356
[Laughs]

23:03.407 --> 23:05.525
Thank you.

23:05.576 --> 23:08.495
Just six months ago, if you had
told me that I would be up here,

23:08.529 --> 23:11.264
I would have
called you crazy.

23:11.298 --> 23:14.617
Tom, Eileen, Ivy,

23:14.652 --> 23:18.254
thank you
for waiting patiently

23:18.289 --> 23:23.159
while I fixed something
that was nearly broken.

23:23.177 --> 23:25.178
I also wanted
to take this opportunity

23:25.212 --> 23:30.216
to acknowledge one of my fellow
nominees, Kyle Bishop.

23:30.251 --> 23:33.052
I only knew him
a short time,

23:33.104 --> 23:37.223
but I was certain that he had
great things ahead of him.

23:37.258 --> 23:42.645
So I would like to dedicate
this award to his memory.

23:42.679 --> 23:48.568
Thank you.
[Applause]

23:48.619 --> 23:50.904
And now, for outstanding
direction of a musical,

23:50.955 --> 23:53.323
I'd like to call up
our co-winners,

23:53.357 --> 23:55.691
Tom Levitt and Derek Wills.

23:55.709 --> 24:00.696
[Applause]

24:00.714 --> 24:03.550
Thank you.

24:03.584 --> 24:05.051
Okay,
this is awkward.

24:05.085 --> 24:07.837
Um, do you want to go first,
kind sir?

24:07.839 --> 24:11.141
Um, you first. I'll finish.
That seems familiar.

24:11.175 --> 24:15.478
Um, do yo[Laughter]go first,
yes, it does. Um, very well.

24:15.513 --> 24:20.533
A great man once said,
"to triumph without risk

24:20.568 --> 24:24.053
is to win without glory,"
and if that's true,

24:24.071 --> 24:27.106
then my journey from safe,
traditional Broadway

24:27.158 --> 24:31.561
to the cutting edge
of east 4th street is...

24:31.579 --> 24:37.083
Probably the greatest triumph
of my professional career.

24:37.117 --> 24:40.103
And I owe
nearly all of it

24:40.137 --> 24:42.622
to this extraordinary company
of young artists,

24:42.673 --> 24:47.710
so I thank them all, and you.
Thank you.

24:47.744 --> 24:53.099
[Applause]

24:53.133 --> 24:57.554
Besides Eileen Rand,
my dear friend Julia Houston,

24:57.588 --> 25:00.756
and the amazing Ivy Lynn,

25:00.774 --> 25:07.113
the person I most want to thank
today is you, Derek.

25:07.147 --> 25:08.898
I wouldn't be standing here
if you hadn't

25:08.932 --> 25:13.236
made that crazy leap
and quit <i>Bombshell.</i>

25:13.270 --> 25:15.989
And even though you and I
go together

25:16.040 --> 25:19.209
about as well
as Lena Dunham and a bra,

25:19.243 --> 25:20.743
uh...
[Laughter]

25:20.777 --> 25:21.794
I've learned
a tremendous amount

25:21.829 --> 25:23.580
about the art of directing
from you.

25:23.614 --> 25:26.032
Since I probably
won't get to make another speech

25:26.066 --> 25:27.734
this award season,

25:27.768 --> 25:31.588
I just wanted to acknowledge
that debt.

25:31.622 --> 25:34.874
This award shouldn't be
half yours.

25:34.909 --> 25:37.594
It's all yours.

25:37.628 --> 25:40.296
[Applause]

25:40.314 --> 25:42.765
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

25:45.603 --> 25:49.405
The OCC
is very proud to award...

25:49.440 --> 25:51.824
Hey, can I talk to you
for a minute?

25:51.859 --> 25:54.494
To Daisy Parker
for <i>Hit List.</i>

25:54.528 --> 25:56.079
[Applause]

25:56.113 --> 26:00.033
[Sighs]

26:00.084 --> 26:03.920
- What do you want?
- To apologize.

26:03.954 --> 26:08.207
What I said about Kyle
and your show was awful.

26:08.259 --> 26:09.676
I wish I could
take it back.

26:09.710 --> 26:12.295
Yeah, well, it's all over
the place now, so too late.

26:12.329 --> 26:13.796
Play the role of the diva,

26:13.830 --> 26:17.050
and to my phenomenal cast
for embracing me...

26:17.101 --> 26:18.834
- Is everything okay over here?
- She can't take back

26:18.852 --> 26:20.503
anything she said either,
now, can she?

26:20.521 --> 26:22.055
- Excuse me?
- You two

26:22.106 --> 26:24.674
are completely messing up
Kyle's chance to be recognized.

26:24.692 --> 26:26.342
I've been nothing
but gracious.

26:26.360 --> 26:27.560
Oh, you're so gracious,
everyone thinks

26:27.611 --> 26:29.062
you wrote the damn show
yourself!

26:29.113 --> 26:30.446
Don't you raise your voice
to Julia. She's...

26:30.481 --> 26:31.731
No, no, no.
I want to know what he means.

26:31.782 --> 26:33.533
You keep talking about
how close you were to Kyle.

26:33.567 --> 26:36.286
- People just assume that...
- Who? Who, the press?

26:36.320 --> 26:37.954
They will twist anything
for a story.

26:37.988 --> 26:40.456
I have done nothing
but support your show,

26:40.491 --> 26:42.659
sometimes to the detriment
of my own.

26:42.693 --> 26:44.577
I supported Kyle.

26:44.628 --> 26:46.348
You want to know
how you can support Kyle?

26:46.363 --> 26:49.031
You tell people that you
did not work on <i>Hit List</i> at all!

26:49.049 --> 26:50.533
But that's not true.

26:50.551 --> 26:52.335
Well, the truth doesn't really
seem to matter, does it, Tom?

26:52.369 --> 26:53.803
If it did,
people would know that

26:53.837 --> 26:55.371
Julia didn't write <i>Bombshell</i>
all by herself either.

26:55.389 --> 26:56.589
- What are you talking about?
- Karen said

26:56.640 --> 26:58.725
you had a dramaturge too,
Peter somebody.

26:58.759 --> 27:00.843
What? No, I said
everyone has dramaturges.

27:00.877 --> 27:02.011
Oh, well,
then Julia won't mind

27:02.045 --> 27:03.479
if I start talking about it,
now, will she?

27:03.514 --> 27:04.931
- Are you threatening me?
- No, he doesn't mean it.

27:04.982 --> 27:06.432
Jimmy, shut up.

27:06.483 --> 27:08.568
Julia doesn't need a lecture
in theatrical ethics from you.

27:08.602 --> 27:10.486
Derek, I don't need
your support,

27:10.521 --> 27:13.723
not after you ripped apart
our "safe, traditional" show.

27:13.741 --> 27:14.774
I did not mean that
as an insult.

27:14.825 --> 27:15.775
What is the matter
with you?

27:15.826 --> 27:17.493
What is going on here?

27:17.528 --> 27:19.895
Please, would you
get back to your seats?

27:19.913 --> 27:22.949
We're professionals here.
My God.

27:23.000 --> 27:26.419
It was a long and difficult
trip from east 4th street.

27:26.453 --> 27:29.455
[Clears throat and sniffs]

27:31.959 --> 27:33.242
What's the matter
with him now?

27:33.260 --> 27:35.712
Derek, he's not been
feeling well. Besides,

27:35.746 --> 27:37.680
you won't have to deal with him
much longer.

27:37.715 --> 27:39.132
What's that
supposed to mean?

27:39.183 --> 27:41.384
Ana knows how you tried
to buy her off with some role.

27:41.418 --> 27:43.386
She's going public.

27:43.420 --> 27:44.554
Congratulations
to all our winners,

27:44.588 --> 27:46.556
and we hope to see you all
here next year.

27:46.590 --> 27:49.425
Thank you, enjoy your day.
[Applause]

27:49.443 --> 27:51.927
Jimmy?
Are you out here?

27:51.945 --> 27:54.430
I know, I know,
I was too hard on Julia.

27:54.448 --> 27:57.066
Jimmy, you're sick.
You're losing your voice.

27:57.100 --> 27:58.401
No.

27:58.435 --> 28:00.903
Your understudy's going on.
You need to rest.

28:00.937 --> 28:02.321
It's the last night
for members

28:02.356 --> 28:03.489
of the Tony nominating
committee,

28:03.540 --> 28:05.158
and they're gonna see me.
[Coughs]

28:05.192 --> 28:06.709
What's the matter?

28:06.744 --> 28:08.378
You afraid they might
like him better?

28:08.412 --> 28:11.164
Oh, come on... I'm not leaving
this theater, Karen, all right?

28:11.215 --> 28:14.584
Okay. Then don't.

28:14.618 --> 28:19.555
- What's that?
- A ticket.

28:19.590 --> 28:23.459
You're gonna sit and watch
what you and Kyle created.

28:31.769 --> 28:33.402
♪ You can't see the hook ♪

28:33.610 --> 28:35.243
♪ We can't sell the look ♪

28:35.294 --> 28:37.879
♪ I hear it every day

28:38.260 --> 28:41.812
♪ you won't be a star
if you're who you are ♪

28:41.847 --> 28:47.818
♪ so I just fade away

28:47.853 --> 28:50.938
♪ make me someone new

28:50.989 --> 28:54.025
♪ tell me what I do

28:54.059 --> 28:58.829
♪ to rewrite this story

28:58.864 --> 29:00.331
♪

29:00.365 --> 29:03.334
[Upbeat Broadway music
and applause]

29:03.368 --> 29:08.522
♪

29:08.557 --> 29:10.591
I gotta get out of here.

29:10.625 --> 29:13.711
- Where are you going?
- Out of town.

29:13.745 --> 29:17.631
Tonight?
What about nominations?

29:17.682 --> 29:20.801
My life has to be
about more than this show.

29:20.852 --> 29:23.804
[Music and singing
in background]

29:23.855 --> 29:27.108
♪

29:35.100 --> 29:36.984
[Sighs]

29:37.035 --> 29:39.537
Hello again.

29:39.571 --> 29:41.655
Our publicist told me
you were here, so...

29:41.706 --> 29:45.493
Well, I'm on the committee.
I had to see the show.

29:45.544 --> 29:50.414
I know I'm breaking probably
every rule, but have to ask,

29:50.448 --> 29:52.800
what'd you think?

29:52.834 --> 29:56.286
Well, you know what they say
about Tony voting?

29:56.304 --> 29:59.957
First, you vote for yourself.
No show this year.

29:59.975 --> 30:02.009
Then you vote against
your enemies.

30:02.060 --> 30:05.012
You, yesterday.

30:05.063 --> 30:07.565
But then
you vote with your heart,

30:07.599 --> 30:09.433
which is what I'm doing
tonight.

30:09.467 --> 30:12.803
I don't know how much support
you have out there,

30:12.821 --> 30:16.107
but you have mine.

30:17.476 --> 30:19.309
Thank you
for being honest.

30:19.327 --> 30:24.314
Patrick Dillon, you gave me
more than a fair shot.

30:24.332 --> 30:25.983
You're very talented,

30:26.001 --> 30:27.618
but when I saw how gracious
you were to Derek,

30:27.652 --> 30:31.589
I thought,
"you deserve it."

30:31.623 --> 30:35.176
- I'm sure I'll see you around.
- Okay.

30:37.829 --> 30:40.097
[Sighs]

30:42.667 --> 30:48.338
Glass closet, my ass.
That door is wide open.

30:48.356 --> 30:49.857
Thank you.

30:49.891 --> 30:51.225
Thanks for coming.
Thank you.

30:51.276 --> 30:53.177
Thank you.

30:53.195 --> 30:54.562
Hi. Who can I make it to?

30:54.613 --> 30:56.614
Jimmy.

30:56.648 --> 30:59.650
- [Laughs] Hey, stupid.
- [Laughs]

30:59.684 --> 31:01.702
What'd you think?

31:01.736 --> 31:03.687
Uh, well,
it was incredible.

31:03.705 --> 31:06.707
[Chuckles]
You were on fire out there.

31:06.741 --> 31:08.358
It's fun.

31:08.376 --> 31:11.795
I felt Kyle.

31:11.830 --> 31:15.132
It was like... I don't know,
it was like he was there.

31:15.167 --> 31:16.967
He is.

31:17.002 --> 31:18.802
People know his name,
Jimmy.

31:18.837 --> 31:21.222
Awards or not,
they'll remember him.

31:21.256 --> 31:23.707
- Yeah.
- Hi.

31:23.725 --> 31:25.392
Hi. Am I interrupting
something?

31:25.427 --> 31:27.811
- No.
- What are you doing here?

31:27.846 --> 31:30.014
I was thinking
about what you said today,

31:30.048 --> 31:35.102
and I wanted you to know
that I'm not gonna lie.

31:35.153 --> 31:39.073
Not about what I did for Kyle
on <i>Hit List,</i>

31:39.107 --> 31:43.227
and not about what Peter
did for me on <i>Bombshell.</i>

31:43.245 --> 31:46.914
Artists shouldn't feel ashamed
about helping each other.

31:46.948 --> 31:48.666
It shouldn't always be
a competition.

31:48.700 --> 31:51.785
You're right.

31:51.836 --> 31:55.739
Well, you helped both of us,
so I'm sorry.

31:55.757 --> 31:58.626
Good luck
with the nominations.

31:58.677 --> 32:01.679
You too.

32:07.469 --> 32:09.603
[Sighs]
Thanks.

32:12.774 --> 32:14.475
Karen.

32:14.526 --> 32:19.930
- Hey. Ana, are you okay?
- I need your help.

32:19.948 --> 32:22.950
Okay.

32:27.572 --> 32:30.541
[Bar music and laughter]

32:30.575 --> 32:36.580
♪

32:37.582 --> 32:39.416
Derek.

32:39.450 --> 32:41.618
Oh, God. Let me guess.

32:41.636 --> 32:46.006
You've come to tell me that
I'm gonna pay for what I did.

32:46.057 --> 32:48.175
No, I'm here to tell you that
you're gonna get away with it.

32:48.226 --> 32:50.811
I had my lawyer
rescind the letter.

32:50.845 --> 32:53.931
I'm gonna take the tour.

32:53.965 --> 32:57.301
Okay.

32:57.319 --> 33:00.437
I'm sorry
how everything worked out.

33:00.471 --> 33:02.990
That's the thing,
I don't think you are.

33:03.024 --> 33:05.475
Otherwise, you wouldn't
keep doing this again and again.

33:05.493 --> 33:07.027
You know, the only way
you would have stopped

33:07.078 --> 33:10.080
is if I would have exposed you
for who you really are,

33:10.115 --> 33:13.984
and that's what's really hard
for me to live with.

33:14.019 --> 33:16.320
Yeah, well, it's hard for me
to live with too.

33:16.338 --> 33:18.672
I'm sure you'll be just fine.
You've had a lot of practice.

33:18.707 --> 33:21.675
Come on, let's go.

33:30.001 --> 33:32.219
Oh, great.
[Sighs]

33:32.270 --> 33:34.555
What, are you up next,
are you?

33:34.606 --> 33:38.309
Come on, then.
Start kicking.

33:38.343 --> 33:40.861
I came to tell you
something important,

33:40.895 --> 33:44.514
but I'm actually glad
they got to you first.

33:44.532 --> 33:47.017
What have I done now?

33:47.035 --> 33:50.654
Uh, Ivy, no, wait.
Listen, let me explain.

33:50.688 --> 33:52.656
I've heard enough.

33:52.690 --> 33:55.025
You've never done
the right thing, Derek,

33:55.043 --> 33:58.045
and you never will.

34:14.601 --> 34:17.418
We did everything possible
to blow these nominations.

34:17.451 --> 34:18.702
I take solace in that.

34:18.753 --> 34:21.388
We didn't go halfway,
it's true.

34:21.422 --> 34:22.656
[Knocking at door]

34:22.690 --> 34:26.458
It's open!
Hurry up, it's coming on.

34:26.493 --> 34:28.494
I brought scones.

34:28.512 --> 34:31.047
And scotch,
in case things go badly.

34:31.098 --> 34:33.166
I don't even know
why I'm watching these.

34:33.199 --> 34:34.751
I'd understand
if you didn't.

34:34.784 --> 34:37.971
[Sighs]
No, I'm pulling for the show,

34:38.005 --> 34:39.172
and for you.

34:39.190 --> 34:40.190
[Knocking at door]

34:40.190 --> 34:42.192
Can you get that?

34:45.228 --> 34:46.780
Oh, hi.

34:46.813 --> 34:48.447
I was hoping you guys
wouldn't mind some company.

34:48.482 --> 34:50.766
Oh, no, of course.
Come in.

34:52.853 --> 34:56.072
- Oh.
- Oh, my God, they're on!

34:56.123 --> 34:58.291
- I'm gonna make it big.
- Here.

34:58.326 --> 34:59.826
- Hey.
- Okay.

34:59.860 --> 35:01.778
And the nominees
for best performance

35:01.812 --> 35:05.131
by an actress in a featured role
in a musical are...

35:05.166 --> 35:08.551
- Leigh Conroy, <i>Bombshell.</i>
- Oh, yay!

35:08.586 --> 35:10.203
Ivy Lynn, <i>Liaisons.</i>

35:10.221 --> 35:13.006
What? What, we were open
like five minutes!

35:13.040 --> 35:15.175
- [Laughs]
- Oh, my God!

35:15.209 --> 35:16.309
Anika Noni Rose,
<i>Imitation of Life.</i>

35:16.344 --> 35:18.178
[Phone ringing]
Of course, that's her.

35:18.212 --> 35:20.430
She probably wants me
to withdraw.

35:20.481 --> 35:22.265
Hi, mom.
Congratulations!

35:22.316 --> 35:24.851
And Daisy Parker,
<i>Hit List.</i>

35:24.885 --> 35:26.186
- What?
- Oh, come on!

35:26.220 --> 35:28.271
Of course.
Just the icing on the cake.

35:28.322 --> 35:30.607
No, this is not over.
I'm getting you that part back.

35:30.658 --> 35:33.944
She's not gonna be here.
She's gonna be on tour.

35:33.995 --> 35:36.613
The nominees
for best choreography are...

35:36.664 --> 35:39.733
Casey Nicholaw,
<i>The gathering storm;</i>

35:39.767 --> 35:43.203
Susan Stroman,
<i>Imitation of Life;</i>

35:43.237 --> 35:48.408
Derek Wills, <i>Bombshell;</i>
And Derek Wills, <i>Hit List</i>.

35:48.426 --> 35:52.095
And the nominees for best book
of a musical are...

35:53.714 --> 35:54.714
Kyle Bishop...

35:54.715 --> 35:56.549
- Oh, my God!
- [Gasps]

35:56.583 --> 35:58.518
- <i>Hit List.</i>
- We did it.

35:58.552 --> 35:59.792
[Laughter]
Harvey Fierstein...

35:59.804 --> 36:01.524
- He did it. [Laughs]
- <i>The gathering storm.</i>

36:01.555 --> 36:03.857
Julia Houston, <i>Bombshell.</i>

36:03.891 --> 36:05.258
[Laughs]

36:05.276 --> 36:06.393
- [Squeals]
- David Lindsay-Abaire,

36:06.427 --> 36:08.311
<i>The last good year.</i>

36:08.362 --> 36:09.696
And Tony fact,

36:09.730 --> 36:12.148
Kyle Bishop
is the youngest person

36:12.199 --> 36:13.900
ever nominated
for this award.

36:13.934 --> 36:15.702
- Original score's next.
- Oh, boy.

36:15.736 --> 36:18.604
The nominees
for best original score,

36:18.622 --> 36:21.825
music and/or lyrics
written for the theater, are..

36:21.859 --> 36:24.444
<i>Bombshell,</i>
music by Tom Levitt,

36:24.462 --> 36:27.163
- [laughter] Lyrics by Julia Houston.
- We're racking 'em up.

36:27.214 --> 36:30.166
<i>Hit List,</i> music and lyrics
by Jimmy Collins.

36:30.201 --> 36:31.718
So is <i>Hit List.</i>

36:31.752 --> 36:34.087
<i>Imitation of life,</i>
music by Jeanine Tesori...

36:34.121 --> 36:35.621
- What's next?
- Lyrics by Tony Kushner.

36:35.639 --> 36:37.390
Both: Director.
- Oh, no.

36:37.425 --> 36:40.626
And the nominees for best
direction of a musical are...

36:40.644 --> 36:41.761
Rob Ashford,
<i>The gathering storm...</i>

36:41.795 --> 36:42.896
It's not gonna happen,
you know it.

36:42.930 --> 36:44.064
We can't hear
if you're talking.

36:44.098 --> 36:47.350
- Tom Levitt, <i>Bombshell.</i>
- [Gasps]

36:47.385 --> 36:50.136
- [Laughs]
- Diane Paulus, <i>Oliver!</i>

36:50.154 --> 36:53.606
And Derek Wills,
<i>Hit List.</i>

36:53.640 --> 36:56.076
And on a historical note,
Derek Wills is only

36:56.110 --> 36:58.528
the second person
in Tony history

36:58.579 --> 37:01.531
to be nominated for three awards
in the same year.

37:01.582 --> 37:03.083
The first one
was Bob Fosse.

37:03.117 --> 37:04.150
That is impressive.

37:04.168 --> 37:05.485
- Wow.
- Whoa.

37:05.503 --> 37:07.820
Now, the nominees
for best performance

37:07.838 --> 37:10.090
by an actress in a leading role
in a musical.

37:14.128 --> 37:18.664
Kate Baldwin, <i>Seesaw,</i>

37:18.682 --> 37:20.350
Karen Cartwright, <i>Hit List.</i>
[Squeals and laughs]

37:20.384 --> 37:21.801
- Oh!
- Oh, my God!

37:21.835 --> 37:23.219
You are nominated
for a Tony!

37:23.270 --> 37:25.305
You are nominated for a Tony!
I know! [Screams]

37:25.339 --> 37:28.141
Sutton Foster, <i>Oliver!</i>

37:28.175 --> 37:31.611
And Audra McDonald,
<i>House of flowers.</i>

37:37.351 --> 37:39.502
It didn't...
It didn't happen.

37:39.537 --> 37:42.572
Wait, that was four,
there's five.

37:42.623 --> 37:45.625
- It's alphabetical.
- That's it, I didn't get it.

37:45.659 --> 37:47.360
Oh, God, I didn't get it.

37:47.378 --> 37:50.380
- [Indistinct mumbling]
- What?

37:50.414 --> 37:52.298
- Wait.
- Whoops, I skipped one.

37:52.333 --> 37:54.334
Ivy Lynn for <i>Bombshell.</i>

37:54.368 --> 37:57.470
Sorry to give you a heart attack, Ivy.
[Laughter]

37:59.390 --> 38:01.724
[Phone ringing]

38:01.759 --> 38:05.145
- Agnes.
- 12 nominations, Eileen,

38:05.179 --> 38:07.764
including one for best musical.
We're back in the game.

38:07.798 --> 38:09.715
Wonderful!
How many for <i>Hit List?</i>

38:09.733 --> 38:12.485
13, but that doesn't
mean anything.

38:12.520 --> 38:14.070
That's just one more
than us.

38:14.105 --> 38:15.822
Well, it'll be
the only one they get.

38:15.856 --> 38:20.160
[Tapping]
Oh, can I call you back?

38:20.194 --> 38:22.278
Sorry you came all this way,
Ms. Rand.

38:22.329 --> 38:24.730
- Nick Felder's no longer here.
- What do you mean?

38:24.748 --> 38:26.899
He was released
three weeks ago.

38:26.917 --> 38:29.902
He's out?

38:34.741 --> 38:36.209
[Sighs]

38:40.747 --> 38:44.417
Well, I'm gonna go
in the other room and...

38:44.435 --> 38:47.937
Eavesdrop.
[Chuckles]

38:58.566 --> 39:00.366
Hey, what you did for me
last night...

39:00.401 --> 39:03.653
That's okay.
You already thanked me.

39:03.704 --> 39:05.989
No, no, that's not
what I'm trying to do.

39:06.040 --> 39:09.359
I owe you
an explanation.

39:09.393 --> 39:14.347
I know that I pushed you away
after Kyle died.

39:14.381 --> 39:16.850
I know.

39:16.884 --> 39:19.785
And I think maybe you think
that it was because

39:19.803 --> 39:23.223
that I was mad about you
and Derek, but I wasn't.

39:23.257 --> 39:29.229
I just was afraid to let
someone else get close to me.

39:29.263 --> 39:33.566
And so I just thought it better
to let you go.

39:33.601 --> 39:37.053
I'm sorry.

39:37.087 --> 39:40.190
Uh, you know,
seeing the show last night

39:40.224 --> 39:42.659
did something else too.

39:42.693 --> 39:47.197
It made me realize
it could live on without me.

39:47.248 --> 39:49.983
- What do you mean?
- I mean that it was still great

39:50.017 --> 39:52.402
even with my understudy,

39:52.436 --> 39:54.654
and it would be great
without you too.

39:54.672 --> 39:58.124
The show stands for itself.
Mmhmm.

39:58.158 --> 39:59.992
Are you going somewhere?

40:00.010 --> 40:01.711
[Laughs]

40:01.762 --> 40:03.379
No, no, I just...

40:03.430 --> 40:07.467
Just thinking
about the future.

40:07.501 --> 40:12.338
Kind of nice knowing that
you're leaving something behind,

40:12.356 --> 40:16.059
no matter what.

40:16.110 --> 40:19.862
Thank you so much.
Have a good one.

40:28.689 --> 40:29.689
[Phone ringing]

40:29.690 --> 40:32.024
It's Frank.

40:32.042 --> 40:34.193
[Phone ringing]

40:34.211 --> 40:36.462
Maybe he's come around
about mediation.

40:36.497 --> 40:38.331
[Phone ringing]

40:38.365 --> 40:39.532
Hello?

40:39.550 --> 40:41.751
- I can't believe you did this.
- Did what?

40:41.802 --> 40:44.704
Hire Eileen Rand's
attorney.

40:44.722 --> 40:47.340
Look,
I was angry the other day,

40:47.374 --> 40:49.008
but I was still considering
my options.

40:49.042 --> 40:50.760
This makes things
so much easier.

40:50.811 --> 40:54.046
- No, no, Frank, I was just...
- Declaring war?

40:54.064 --> 40:55.715
You're the one
who had the affair.

40:55.733 --> 40:58.318
It happened. Julia,
this isn't a no-fault divorce.

40:58.352 --> 41:00.820
It is your fault,
and you are gonna pay for it,

41:00.854 --> 41:03.856
and I am gonna take you
for everything you're worth!

41:08.929 --> 41:10.896
Three nominations today.

41:10.914 --> 41:12.665
You are the hottest director
on Broadway.

41:12.700 --> 41:14.917
- Mm.
- What a year of vindication

41:14.952 --> 41:18.004
for you for those allegations
last fall.

41:18.038 --> 41:20.473
Anything you want to say?

41:20.507 --> 41:24.761
Well, as my good friend
Ronnie Moore always says,

41:24.795 --> 41:27.913
the work is the only thing
that matters.

41:27.931 --> 41:32.352
Doesn't matter if it's Broadway
or a black box at the Fringe.

41:32.386 --> 41:36.539
If you stick to that rule,
you'll probably be okay.

41:36.573 --> 41:39.192
Well, I guess we were
all wrong about you.

41:39.226 --> 41:41.577
Mm.

41:41.612 --> 41:46.149
What is it?

41:46.183 --> 41:49.986
Uh...

41:50.037 --> 41:52.705
Actually, you weren't.

42:04.117 --> 42:08.087
Uh, I promised Daisy Parker

42:08.121 --> 42:10.089
the role of the diva
in <i>Hit List</i>

42:10.124 --> 42:14.761
if she would sleep with me.

42:14.795 --> 42:19.599
She made good,
and so did I.

42:19.633 --> 42:22.435
Ana Vargas
was collateral damage.

42:22.469 --> 42:27.290
And wrongfully terminated.

42:27.324 --> 42:30.343
I'm sorry.

