♪ under pressure

45:39.547 --> 45:41.548
♪

45:41.599 --> 45:43.299
♪ pressure

45:43.333 --> 45:47.554
♪

45:47.605 --> 45:51.641
[Finger snaps]

45:51.675 --> 45:53.226
[Pulling back shades]
Tom! Ready to work?

45:53.277 --> 45:56.345
Only 12 hours
till the Tonys.

45:56.363 --> 45:58.181
Oh.

45:58.199 --> 45:59.449
[Playing piano]
Well, the Tony number

45:59.483 --> 46:02.569
is finished, but... just when
we thought we were done.

46:02.620 --> 46:03.620
[Stops playing]

46:03.621 --> 46:05.521
Now, we have to write
a speech.

46:05.539 --> 46:08.658
Not any the old speech,
an acceptance speech.

46:08.692 --> 46:10.359
Think we have a chance?

46:10.377 --> 46:13.997
Okay, I brought programs
from all the nominated shows.

46:14.031 --> 46:15.215
What do you think?

46:15.249 --> 46:17.050
<i>Last good year.</i>
Love Pasek and Paul.

46:17.084 --> 46:18.718
- Mm-hmm.
- <i>Imitation of life.</i>

46:18.752 --> 46:21.304
Pretentious.
I cried like a baby.

46:21.338 --> 46:23.723
- [Laughs]
- <i>Gathering storm,</i> snoozeville.

46:23.757 --> 46:28.144
How would you know?
Agnes said you very distracted.

46:28.179 --> 46:29.479
My future husband
was sitting behind me.

46:29.513 --> 46:31.514
Your future husband
isn't even gay.

46:31.548 --> 46:34.934
Tell that
to his upper arms-s-s.

46:34.969 --> 46:37.770
- Is this something?
- It's from my lawyer.

46:37.822 --> 46:40.473
I was supposed to write
a detailed account

46:40.508 --> 46:43.059
of my history
with Michael Swift

46:43.077 --> 46:46.830
to hopefully put an end
to Frank's case against me.

46:46.864 --> 46:50.917
And I feel like it just
makes his case stronger.

46:52.286 --> 46:54.287
Frank really thinks
you were in love with Michael

46:54.338 --> 46:57.507
from the time you met him?
Yes.

46:57.541 --> 46:58.908
You know that I wasn't,
right?

46:58.926 --> 47:02.679
- Of course.
- Or was I?

47:02.713 --> 47:04.564
So who should we thank?

47:04.598 --> 47:07.383
I want to thank Peter stone
and Tom wopat,

47:07.417 --> 47:09.252
a great, great leading man
who I...

47:09.270 --> 47:11.971
You see how appropriately
gracious I was.

47:12.022 --> 47:14.257
So gracious
you forgot to thank me.

47:14.275 --> 47:18.478
I thanked you in person,
that's better.

47:18.529 --> 47:21.030
If you can tear up a little,
they love it.

47:21.065 --> 47:24.117
I don't need any pointers,
because I'm not gonna win.

47:24.151 --> 47:26.769
I'm nominated twice.
That always splits the vote.

47:26.787 --> 47:28.538
With me in the running,
they're not gonna vote for you

47:28.572 --> 47:31.708
for featured.
You'll win lead, as you should.

47:31.850 --> 47:33.939
Is that the dress you're wearing tonight?

47:33.944 --> 47:36.796
What happened? That fit you
perfectly last week.

47:36.830 --> 47:39.632
It's fine. It's just stuck.
I'll get it.

47:41.585 --> 47:43.736
Have you been
stress eating again?

47:43.771 --> 47:46.122
Now's not the time
to get fat, my dear.

47:46.140 --> 47:48.892
[Chuckles]

47:48.926 --> 47:53.863
I remember the day after
I won my first one.

47:53.898 --> 47:56.933
My career
just skyrocketed.

47:56.967 --> 47:59.802
I had so many offers,
I didn't know what to do.

47:59.837 --> 48:02.205
I was thinking about
maybe taking some time off.

48:02.239 --> 48:03.973
That's exactly
what you can't do.

48:04.008 --> 48:06.576
You have to dive in.
It's all about momentum.

48:06.610 --> 48:10.797
You lose that,
you may never get it again.

48:10.831 --> 48:15.501
[Laughs]
Take time off!

48:15.536 --> 48:19.589
What's gotten into you?

48:19.623 --> 48:22.208
[Signs]

48:22.259 --> 48:24.027
[Elevator dings]

48:24.061 --> 48:25.228
Hi.

48:25.262 --> 48:29.015
Juice, coffee,
shaving cream.

48:32.336 --> 48:34.520
What? I told you
I was bringing supplies.

48:34.555 --> 48:36.406
I thought you meant
more booze.

48:36.440 --> 48:39.008
Yeah, well, that you seem
capable of getting yourself.

48:39.043 --> 48:41.594
They deliver.

48:41.629 --> 48:43.112
So you've been in this room
the whole time?

48:43.147 --> 48:45.898
Just... just gonna
stay in here forever?

48:45.950 --> 48:47.650
It's your third time
you've been at this.

48:47.684 --> 48:49.402
I thought after the first time,
I'd scared you off.

48:49.453 --> 48:51.404
Yeah, well,
I'm worried about you.

48:51.455 --> 48:54.791
Don't be,
I deserve it.

48:54.825 --> 48:57.460
Did all the things
I said I did.

48:57.494 --> 48:59.746
Remember what you said
in Boston?

48:59.797 --> 49:03.199
"The more you hurt,
the better."

49:03.233 --> 49:05.668
I just said that
to get you onstage.

49:05.703 --> 49:08.137
Well, it worked.

49:08.172 --> 49:11.874
And I'm glad I did it.

49:11.892 --> 49:16.429
This will pass,
but you have to let it.

49:16.480 --> 49:19.482
Do I really?

49:21.986 --> 49:24.587
[Pouring liquid]
You can see yourself out.

49:33.475 --> 49:34.809
Five, six, seven.

49:34.860 --> 49:36.560
♪ Hate to break it
♪ hate to break you

49:36.594 --> 49:39.397
♪ hate to break you
♪ I'm not sorry

49:39.431 --> 49:41.282
♪

49:41.316 --> 49:42.700
Uh, what's going on?

49:42.734 --> 49:44.535
I thought we were doing
<i>Voice in a dream</i> for Tonys.

49:44.569 --> 49:47.204
So did I
until they called me in.

49:47.239 --> 49:48.322
Jimmy didn't want
to perform,

49:48.357 --> 49:49.890
so Jerry thought
this was a good substitute.

49:49.925 --> 49:51.325
Stop. Stop.

49:51.376 --> 49:53.878
- What is it, Daisy?
- Jodie is a beat behind.

49:53.912 --> 49:56.613
It's bad enough we have to
work with her every night.

49:56.632 --> 49:57.965
Now we have to go
on national television

49:58.000 --> 49:59.283
and help her look good?

50:00.952 --> 50:03.671
Ugh, it's disgusting.

50:03.722 --> 50:05.723
Hey, can I make
a quick call?

50:05.757 --> 50:07.558
Yeah. Five minutes,
then you're in.

50:14.433 --> 50:15.716
- Hi.
- Hey.

50:15.751 --> 50:18.235
- Tony rehearsal?
- Yeah.

50:18.270 --> 50:21.238
- <i>Let's be bad.</i>
<i>- I'm not sorry.</i>

50:21.273 --> 50:22.740
- With Daisy Parker?
- Mm.

50:22.774 --> 50:25.493
Ooh. Speaking of,
is Derek in there?

50:25.527 --> 50:28.746
Uh, no. He hasn't
left his place in weeks.

50:28.780 --> 50:31.365
And I've... I've tried
to pull him out of it,

50:31.400 --> 50:34.869
but I don't have
the magic touch,

50:34.920 --> 50:36.754
not like you did,
anyway.

50:36.788 --> 50:38.655
I'm sure
he'll get it together.

50:38.674 --> 50:41.959
Yeah, I'm not so sure.
He's in a pretty dark place.

50:41.993 --> 50:44.211
I've never seen him
like this before.

50:44.262 --> 50:46.397
Hey, I forgot to ask,

50:46.431 --> 50:48.499
can you remind Jimmy to pick up
his tickets for tonight?

50:48.517 --> 50:50.301
He has until 3:00
or he's gonna lose them.

50:50.335 --> 50:51.352
He hasn't picked up
his tickets?

50:51.386 --> 50:52.887
Wow, that's
cutting it close.

50:52.938 --> 50:54.438
Can you make your phone call
and come back?

50:54.473 --> 50:57.391
Daisy just corrected Lexi
on her one line.

50:57.442 --> 50:59.009
Not pretty in there.
Ugh.

50:59.027 --> 51:01.562
Okay.
Thanks.

51:01.613 --> 51:03.847
I don't know how you can
work with that girl.

51:03.865 --> 51:05.649
We have to.

51:05.683 --> 51:09.370
I'm not so sure about that.
You guys outnumber her.

51:09.404 --> 51:10.654
If you don't want
to perform with her,

51:10.688 --> 51:14.041
you shouldn't have to.

51:14.076 --> 51:16.360
Hey, I hadn't
thought about that.

51:16.378 --> 51:18.379
See ya.

51:20.482 --> 51:23.250
[Line ringing]

51:23.301 --> 51:25.920
Hey. How's it going
over there?

51:25.954 --> 51:28.122
I'm not gonna lie.
It's a little strange.

51:28.156 --> 51:29.640
We're doing
<i>I'm not sorry.</i>

51:29.674 --> 51:32.343
Yeah, Jerry thought
that would be a better choice.

51:32.377 --> 51:34.378
Are you getting cold feet
about tonight?

51:34.396 --> 51:36.180
What?

51:36.214 --> 51:39.950
Well, Marissa said
that you didn't want to perform.

51:39.985 --> 51:42.353
So I just... I got
a weird feeling about it.

51:42.387 --> 51:45.356
- I'm fine. Um...
- Okay.

51:45.390 --> 51:48.058
Why don't you pick me up
tonight? We can go together.

51:48.076 --> 51:49.577
I was just gonna go
from here, so...

51:49.611 --> 51:53.547
My place at 6:00.
Don't be late.

51:53.582 --> 51:56.083
Yeah, okay.

51:58.837 --> 52:03.407
Looks good.

52:03.425 --> 52:07.511
Where should I send
your deposit?

52:07.546 --> 52:10.548
Keep it.

52:17.355 --> 52:19.356
Rene, come on.

52:23.228 --> 52:25.446
How'd you find me?
I knew where you were.

52:25.480 --> 52:28.098
I was gonna leave you alone,
since that's what you wanted.

52:28.116 --> 52:31.652
What I wanted was to not
complicate your life anymore.

52:31.703 --> 52:35.439
You're the only thing that's
clear in my life right now.

52:38.210 --> 52:40.628
What's that?

52:40.662 --> 52:46.250
Win or lose,
I want you next to me tonight.

52:46.284 --> 52:47.751
[Phone dialing]

52:47.785 --> 52:49.587
Jerry,
I need to talk to you.

52:49.621 --> 52:51.222
They refuse
to do the number.

52:51.256 --> 52:54.058
What, the entire company,
you're telling me?

52:54.092 --> 52:57.244
Karen, Gabe, Lexi,
all the dancers. It's a coup.

52:57.279 --> 52:58.395
Well,
they don't want to perform,

52:58.430 --> 53:00.064
they don't have to perform.

53:00.098 --> 53:02.600
You just got yourself a solo
on the Tonys.

53:02.634 --> 53:06.437
I think <i>Reach for me</i>
would be great, don't you?

53:06.471 --> 53:11.192
I'll make the call.

53:11.243 --> 53:15.112
Nice place. Wow.
These all yours?

53:15.146 --> 53:17.031
Yup.

53:17.082 --> 53:19.366
Except that one.
That was Kyle's.

53:19.401 --> 53:21.335
He left it here.

53:21.369 --> 53:24.455
He spent the night a few times.
I guess I never told you that.

53:24.489 --> 53:27.124
No, you most certainly
did not.

53:27.158 --> 53:30.377
- I knew. [Laughs]
- You did?

53:30.412 --> 53:34.632
[Laughing] Yeah.
I mean, he really liked you.

53:34.666 --> 53:36.383
I really liked him too.

53:36.434 --> 53:40.337
[Tea kettle whistling]
Tea's ready.

53:42.691 --> 53:44.508
Look, I know
what he meant to you,

53:44.526 --> 53:48.028
but I really hope that
you'll find another partner

53:48.063 --> 53:49.063
and keep writing.

53:49.114 --> 53:52.399
Maybe not now,
but in the future.

53:52.450 --> 53:58.188
You have a gift.
You can't let that go to waste.

53:58.206 --> 54:01.858
So what's the favor
you wanted to ask me?

54:01.877 --> 54:05.579
Um...

54:05.630 --> 54:07.798
If...

54:07.832 --> 54:11.819
Kyle wins tonight, um...

54:11.853 --> 54:16.807
I was just hoping maybe
you could accept it for him.

54:16.841 --> 54:20.177
Are you not gonna
be there?

54:20.211 --> 54:21.679
Jimmy,
what are you doing?

54:21.713 --> 54:25.716
Look, this is your moment.
You can't miss it.

54:25.734 --> 54:28.852
Stop sabotaging yourself.
Whatever makes you do that,

54:28.886 --> 54:32.356
it's time to face it,
once and for all.

54:32.390 --> 54:35.075
It's not too late.

54:40.949 --> 54:46.537
- Good luck... good luck tonight.
- You too.

55:00.512 --> 55:02.847
<i>You can leave it on the table.</i>

55:02.881 --> 55:06.884
[Footsteps approaching]

55:11.523 --> 55:14.075
Oh, my God. What...

55:14.109 --> 55:17.528
What is the point
of having a bloody doorman?

55:17.563 --> 55:19.680
Well,
you don't look good.

55:19.698 --> 55:22.567
Yeah, well...
[Grunts]

55:22.618 --> 55:24.902
Look, I know you haven't had
a good couple of weeks.

55:24.953 --> 55:28.239
Oh, yeah, you think?

55:28.290 --> 55:31.475
No, I'm done, all right?

55:31.510 --> 55:33.193
My agent
won't talk to me,

55:33.212 --> 55:34.512
not a theater in town
will touch me.

55:34.546 --> 55:36.047
The...

55:36.081 --> 55:39.467
The guys that deliver this,
they won't look me in the eye.

55:39.501 --> 55:42.119
So, no, I have not had
a good few weeks.

55:42.154 --> 55:44.672
Why did you do it?

55:44.706 --> 55:46.841
[Chuckles]

55:48.376 --> 55:54.232
Do you know what I actually do?
I bluff.

55:54.266 --> 55:56.484
All day long.

55:56.518 --> 56:00.705
What do I know, eh?

56:00.739 --> 56:03.791
It's pretty lonely.

56:03.825 --> 56:07.194
I always thought
you knew that.

56:07.229 --> 56:10.298
I do.

56:10.332 --> 56:16.871
I'm tired, Ivy, all right?
I'm so tired.

56:16.905 --> 56:19.907
It's not all gone.

56:21.510 --> 56:25.579
Am I gonna see you there
tonight?

56:25.597 --> 56:28.099
Oh, yeah, for sure.
Yeah.

56:28.133 --> 56:29.634
Yeah, spending the evening
in a room

56:29.685 --> 56:31.919
full of sanctimonious pricks
who've got it in for me?

56:31.954 --> 56:33.404
Yeah, I'll be there.

56:33.438 --> 56:35.806
I don't want to be there
without you.

56:35.857 --> 56:39.393
I know I hurt you.

56:39.427 --> 56:42.780
And you hurt me too.

56:42.814 --> 56:45.249
But that doesn't mean
I don't love you.

56:49.288 --> 56:52.123
I'll see you there.

56:54.209 --> 56:56.944
Oh, and...

56:56.962 --> 56:58.729
Take a shower.

56:58.764 --> 57:01.782
Smells like a dive bar
in here.

57:12.728 --> 57:14.679
Why am I here?

57:14.730 --> 57:16.797
Uh,
[Clears throat].

57:16.832 --> 57:21.819
This is the letter my lawyer
asked me to give to you.

57:26.575 --> 57:29.477
I don't understand.

57:29.511 --> 57:32.730
What's going on, Julia?

57:32.764 --> 57:34.832
I told someone today
that this was their moment

57:34.866 --> 57:36.617
to face the truth,

57:36.651 --> 57:38.536
and if I'm gonna give
that kind of advice,

57:38.570 --> 57:41.672
I need to do the same.

57:41.707 --> 57:44.709
I met Michael
years before you knew I did.

57:44.760 --> 57:48.980
I didn't sleep with him,

57:49.014 --> 57:53.267
but I thought about it,
and him, a lot.

57:55.554 --> 58:00.091
And I never really
let it go.

58:00.125 --> 58:03.811
For much of our marriage,
he was there.

58:03.845 --> 58:05.846
[Chuckles]

58:09.368 --> 58:12.319
I see.

58:12.354 --> 58:16.356
And it wasn't because
I didn't love you.

58:18.877 --> 58:21.078
I just didn't love you
the right way.

58:26.334 --> 58:29.170
So I'm not gonna
give you this letter.

58:29.204 --> 58:31.672
[Clears throat]

58:31.706 --> 58:36.977
I think that you should do
whatever you want...

58:37.012 --> 58:40.014
Concerning the settlement.

58:40.048 --> 58:44.051
I won't refute anything.

58:44.069 --> 58:47.071
Julia.

58:50.942 --> 58:52.960
Thank you.

58:55.914 --> 58:58.899
[Pop music playing]

58:58.917 --> 59:02.119
Okay, it is actually not fair
how beautiful you look.

59:02.170 --> 59:04.955
Oh, what's not fair is
you're not going too.

59:05.006 --> 59:07.908
Oh, believe me,
I'm gonna cry after you leave.

59:07.926 --> 59:10.244
- Is he not here?
- No.

59:10.262 --> 59:12.847
Sorry.

59:12.881 --> 59:14.748
Yeah, I have to stop
feeling this way.

59:14.766 --> 59:17.551
Look, forget about him.
You are a Tony nominee.

59:17.585 --> 59:20.354
No matter what happens, no one
can take that away from you.

59:20.388 --> 59:22.389
Google "Karen Cartwright,"
and that's what's gonna come up

59:22.423 --> 59:24.558
from now until the end of time.
I know.

59:24.592 --> 59:26.894
I just wish he'd come through,
just once.

59:26.928 --> 59:28.729
[Knocking at door]

59:31.483 --> 59:33.284
I'm late.

59:33.318 --> 59:35.202
I noticed.

59:35.237 --> 59:36.537
You didn't think
I'd show.

59:36.571 --> 59:39.323
Well, you don't have
a very good track record.

59:39.374 --> 59:42.993
[Chuckles]
Why aren't you dressed?

59:43.044 --> 59:45.329
What are you
talking about?

59:45.380 --> 59:48.632
Well, I mean,
this is Kyle's ticket.

59:48.667 --> 59:51.302
You didn't think he'd want us
to go without you, did you?

59:51.336 --> 59:52.670
- Oh!
- Really?

59:52.721 --> 59:54.472
- Yeah.
- Oh, my God!

59:54.506 --> 59:55.890
- Okay, I need 15 minutes.
- Go!

59:55.924 --> 59:57.124
All right, I'm sorry!
Thank you!

59:57.142 --> 59:58.342
- [Laughs]
- Stay just a second

59:58.393 --> 59:59.560
and help her
with her hair.

59:59.594 --> 01:00:01.061
Hey, I think I have something
in the closet.

01:00:01.096 --> 01:00:03.797
Um, hey. Thanks.

01:00:05.150 --> 01:00:08.319
♪ How ya doing?
I think I'm gonna stay awhile ♪

01:00:08.353 --> 01:00:10.237
[Phone ringing]

01:00:10.272 --> 01:00:13.240
Hello?

01:00:13.275 --> 01:00:15.526
Yes, yes, I will be there
before midnight.

01:00:15.577 --> 01:00:19.580
Thank you. Thank you so much
for giving me the night.

01:00:22.150 --> 01:00:23.534
Have you worn
the red one before?

01:00:25.425 --> 01:00:27.124
[Fanfare]

01:00:27.893 --> 01:00:32.147
Welcome to the 67th annual
Tony awards,

01:00:32.181 --> 01:00:35.299
coming to you live
from New York City.

01:00:35.317 --> 01:00:37.685
♪

01:00:37.736 --> 01:00:39.604
- What's gotten into you?
- Nothing.

01:00:39.638 --> 01:00:42.073
Just feel great, that's all.
[Chuckles]

01:00:42.107 --> 01:00:43.975
Well, you should.
It's your night.

01:00:43.993 --> 01:00:45.743
Both: [Laughs]
- Lillias White.

01:00:45.778 --> 01:00:48.112
[Cheers and applause]

01:00:48.147 --> 01:00:49.864
Have you practiced?

01:00:49.915 --> 01:00:52.417
My speech?
No. I'm not winning.

01:00:52.451 --> 01:00:54.202
No, your losing face
when I win.

01:00:54.253 --> 01:00:56.320
Here, try this one.

01:00:56.338 --> 01:00:58.139
[Sighs]
The nominees

01:00:58.174 --> 01:01:02.260
for best performance
of an actress in a musical

01:01:02.294 --> 01:01:05.496
in a featured role are...
[Gasps]

01:01:05.514 --> 01:01:07.832
Leigh Conroy, <i>Bombshell.</i>

01:01:07.850 --> 01:01:10.385
[Applause]

01:01:10.436 --> 01:01:13.271
Ivy Lynn, <i>Liaisons.</i>

01:01:13.305 --> 01:01:16.641
[Applause]

01:01:16.675 --> 01:01:20.778
Anika Noni Rose,
<i>Imitation of life.</i>

01:01:20.813 --> 01:01:23.064
[Applause]

01:01:23.115 --> 01:01:27.485
And Daisy Parker,
<i>Hit List.</i>

01:01:27.519 --> 01:01:30.738
[Applause]

01:01:30.789 --> 01:01:33.575
And the Tony goes to...

01:01:33.626 --> 01:01:35.710
Daisy Parker, <i>Hit List.</i>

01:01:35.744 --> 01:01:38.830
[Applause and upbeat music]

01:01:38.864 --> 01:01:42.417
This is <i>Hit List's</i> fifth award
of the evening.

01:01:42.468 --> 01:01:44.636
Good thing you got to practice
that face, huh?

01:01:44.670 --> 01:01:47.171
Wow, I can' believe it.

01:01:47.205 --> 01:01:50.541
And now, Tony award winner,
Ron Rifkin.

01:01:50.559 --> 01:01:52.310
It's so loud in here,
I can hardly hear

01:01:52.344 --> 01:01:53.895
the crazy thoughts
in my head.

01:01:53.929 --> 01:01:55.179
You got it in the bag.

01:01:55.213 --> 01:01:57.899
The nominees for best book
of a musical are...

01:01:57.933 --> 01:02:01.385
Oh, is it possible I want
Kyle to win instead of me?

01:02:01.403 --> 01:02:04.856
I mean, could I actually be
that selfless?

01:02:04.890 --> 01:02:09.393
Historically, no,
but people change.

01:02:09.411 --> 01:02:11.496
Kyle Bishop, <i>Hit List.</i>

01:02:11.530 --> 01:02:14.165
[Applause]

01:02:14.199 --> 01:02:17.068
Julia Houston, <i>Bombshell.</i>

01:02:17.086 --> 01:02:18.736
[Applause]

01:02:18.754 --> 01:02:20.394
This is taking forever.
Why... why is it...

01:02:20.405 --> 01:02:22.423
Talk faster, come on!
You sound like Kyle.

01:02:22.458 --> 01:02:23.458
Ugh!

01:02:23.509 --> 01:02:25.677
<i>The last good year.</i>

01:02:25.711 --> 01:02:26.928
[Applause]

01:02:26.962 --> 01:02:30.014
And the Tony goes to...

01:02:30.049 --> 01:02:33.051
Kyle Bishop, <i>Hit List.</i>

01:02:33.085 --> 01:02:35.136
[Sobs]

01:02:35.187 --> 01:02:37.188
He did it.
[Laughs]

01:02:37.222 --> 01:02:42.143
Accepting for Kyle Bishop
is Jimmy Collins.

01:02:42.194 --> 01:02:45.863
[Cheers and applause]

01:02:45.898 --> 01:02:49.117
- You okay?
- Yeah.

01:02:49.151 --> 01:02:53.154
But it turns out
that I actually did want it.

01:03:02.648 --> 01:03:06.417
God, he would've loved this.
[Chuckles and sniffs]

01:03:06.451 --> 01:03:09.887
He would've loved it
because he loved Broadway.

01:03:09.922 --> 01:03:14.175
He... he even used to keep
this collection of <i>Playbills</i>

01:03:14.209 --> 01:03:17.895
from... from shows
that flopped,

01:03:17.930 --> 01:03:20.398
and he would carry them
around with him

01:03:20.432 --> 01:03:22.133
everywhere that he went.

01:03:22.167 --> 01:03:24.519
He pulled extra shifts
for two weeks

01:03:24.570 --> 01:03:28.439
just to save up enough money
to buy a train ticket to Boston

01:03:28.473 --> 01:03:30.942
to see this one.

01:03:30.976 --> 01:03:34.812
And I-I remember,
when he came back.

01:03:34.830 --> 01:03:36.948
Well, he said the show
needed some work...

01:03:36.982 --> 01:03:42.870
[Laughter]
But... but that it was magical.

01:03:42.921 --> 01:03:47.792
And that there was
this girl in it.

01:03:47.826 --> 01:03:53.715
This girl that could
make you smile, and...

01:03:53.766 --> 01:03:56.884
Break your heart
in the same second.

01:03:56.919 --> 01:03:59.637
She signed this for him
a month later at the bar,

01:03:59.671 --> 01:04:04.726
and that is the only reason
that I am standing here tonight,

01:04:04.777 --> 01:04:11.482
so thank you. Thank you all
for giving Kyle something...

01:04:11.516 --> 01:04:15.570
To love... his whole life,

01:04:15.621 --> 01:04:19.741
and... well,
you were right, Julia.

01:04:19.792 --> 01:04:21.743
[Sniffs]
It's never too late. Thanks.

01:04:21.794 --> 01:04:27.799
[Cheers and applause]

01:04:39.728 --> 01:04:42.997
Now, I am happy to present
the Tony award

01:04:43.032 --> 01:04:44.315
for the best original score,

01:04:44.349 --> 01:04:47.384
music and/or lyrics
written for the theater.

01:04:47.403 --> 01:04:49.604
The nominees...

01:04:49.655 --> 01:04:55.226
Bombshell, music by Tom Levitt,
lyrics by Julia Houston.

01:04:55.244 --> 01:04:59.730
<i>Hit List,</i> music and lyrics
by Jimmy Collins.

01:04:59.748 --> 01:05:01.582
Big night for <i>Hit List.</i>

01:05:01.617 --> 01:05:03.567
I'm starting to feel
like they deserve it.

01:05:03.585 --> 01:05:06.204
They spent the last year
fighting like high schoolers.

01:05:06.238 --> 01:05:09.207
- Now they're a team.
- We were them once.

01:05:09.241 --> 01:05:10.758
You saying we aren't
anymore?

01:05:10.793 --> 01:05:13.544
I'm saying Jimmy deserves
original score,

01:05:13.578 --> 01:05:15.746
and we deserve cocktails
with olives in them.

01:05:15.764 --> 01:05:17.515
- [Laughs]
- Several.

01:05:17.549 --> 01:05:18.883
I want a drink
in a coconut.

01:05:18.917 --> 01:05:20.417
Where can we get that?
The winner is... <i>Bombshell.</i>

01:05:20.436 --> 01:05:21.853
Is there still a trader vic's
in New York?

01:05:21.887 --> 01:05:24.856
Like in that midtown hotel?

01:05:24.890 --> 01:05:27.859
[Awards music]

01:05:27.893 --> 01:05:30.194
Julia.

01:05:30.229 --> 01:05:33.898
Both:
[Laugh]

01:05:33.932 --> 01:05:36.267
Oh, my goodness!

01:05:36.285 --> 01:05:39.070
This is <i>Bombshell's</i>
second award of the night,

01:05:39.104 --> 01:05:42.707
having won earlier
for best costume design.

01:05:42.741 --> 01:05:45.827
We wrote a speech,
but completely forgot it.

01:05:45.878 --> 01:05:49.297
- Is true, so all we can say is thank you.
- Thank you so much.

01:05:49.331 --> 01:05:52.300
[Awards music
and cheers and applause]

01:05:52.334 --> 01:05:58.339
♪

01:06:00.476 --> 01:06:03.478
Eh, it's okay.
I got the one I wanted.

01:06:05.630 --> 01:06:10.017
And now, Tony winner
Kathleen Marshall.

01:06:10.068 --> 01:06:13.354
The nominees
for best choreography are...

01:06:13.388 --> 01:06:18.359
Casey Nicholaw
for <i>The gathering storm.</i>

01:06:18.410 --> 01:06:21.445
Susan Stroman
for <i>Imitation of life.</i>

01:06:21.480 --> 01:06:22.914
I can't believe
Derek didn't come.

01:06:22.948 --> 01:06:24.468
- How can he not be here?
- Maybe because

01:06:24.482 --> 01:06:25.833
he didn't want
to experience this.

01:06:25.868 --> 01:06:27.702
Derek Wills for <i>Bombshell.</i>

01:06:27.753 --> 01:06:29.787
[Booing and light applause]

01:06:29.821 --> 01:06:30.922
Maybe it's for the best.

01:06:30.956 --> 01:06:32.957
And Derek Wills
for <i>Hit List.</i>

01:06:32.991 --> 01:06:34.142
[Hissing and light applause]

01:06:34.176 --> 01:06:37.228
Yeah. Definitely good
he's not here.

01:06:37.262 --> 01:06:39.096
And the Tony goes to...

01:06:39.131 --> 01:06:42.383
If we don't win this one,
we're dead.

01:06:42.434 --> 01:06:43.885
We're going to win.
We're going to win.

01:06:43.936 --> 01:06:44.936
[Whispering]
We're going to win.

01:06:44.970 --> 01:06:46.337
- Derek Wills...
All: [Gasp]

01:06:46.355 --> 01:06:47.588
For <i>Hit List.</i>

01:06:47.623 --> 01:06:48.623
[Awards music]

01:06:48.624 --> 01:06:50.674
This is bad.
We now lost six.

01:06:50.692 --> 01:06:51.893
It's over.

01:06:51.944 --> 01:06:53.895
Stop saying that.
It's not over.

01:06:53.946 --> 01:06:55.679
Apparently,
Derek isn't here.

01:06:55.697 --> 01:07:00.117
Uh, yeah, he is. Hey.

01:07:00.152 --> 01:07:01.819
♪

01:07:04.022 --> 01:07:06.791
Okay, um, firstly,

01:07:06.825 --> 01:07:08.042
I would like to thank
the Tony voters

01:07:08.076 --> 01:07:11.078
for judging the work...
And not the man.

01:07:11.113 --> 01:07:13.864
And I'd like
to dedicate this award

01:07:13.882 --> 01:07:15.967
to someone
who I love very much.

01:07:16.001 --> 01:07:17.335
Ivy Lynn.

01:07:17.369 --> 01:07:19.053
She convinced me
to come here tonight.

01:07:19.087 --> 01:07:20.638
I owe her everything.

01:07:20.672 --> 01:07:23.841
Oh... my... God.

01:07:23.875 --> 01:07:24.926
[Chuckles]

01:07:24.977 --> 01:07:27.511
[Light applause]

01:07:27.545 --> 01:07:29.680
And now, please welcome
the cast of <i>Bombshell,</i>

01:07:29.714 --> 01:07:31.649
performing <i>Let's be bad.</i>

01:07:31.683 --> 01:07:33.234
[Laughs]

01:07:33.268 --> 01:07:36.270
<i>[Let's be bad</i> playing]

01:07:39.567 --> 01:07:41.234
<i>Wow.
I can't believe it.</i>

01:07:43.522 --> 01:07:47.792
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:07:47.827 --> 01:07:49.911
Where's Daisy?

01:07:49.962 --> 01:07:54.049
Didn't you hear?
She won.

01:07:54.083 --> 01:07:55.450
Listen,
about what you said...

01:07:55.485 --> 01:08:00.472
Hey, um...
Can we talk about that later?

01:08:00.506 --> 01:08:01.506
Okay.

01:08:01.507 --> 01:08:06.811
[Cheers and applause]

01:08:06.846 --> 01:08:09.097
Darling, come with me.

01:08:09.148 --> 01:08:12.567
Karen as well, just...
Let's go. Quickly, let's go.

01:08:12.602 --> 01:08:15.570
What are we doing?

01:08:15.605 --> 01:08:18.189
Making it right.

01:08:19.242 --> 01:08:21.243
[Sighs]

01:08:24.897 --> 01:08:28.116
[Unfastening latch]

01:08:28.167 --> 01:08:30.234
There's been
a change of plan.

01:08:30.252 --> 01:08:32.002
What are you doing?

01:08:32.037 --> 01:08:35.090
Something I should have done
a long time ago...

01:08:35.124 --> 01:08:36.457
Taking you out.

01:08:36.509 --> 01:08:38.376
You can't do that.

01:08:38.410 --> 01:08:40.078
Weren't you listening?

01:08:40.095 --> 01:08:42.247
Everyone out there
hates me,

01:08:42.265 --> 01:08:44.249
so I can do pretty much
anything I feel like.

01:08:44.267 --> 01:08:45.884
Coming back
from commercial...

01:08:45.917 --> 01:08:49.888
Let's see what Jerry
has to say about it.

01:08:49.921 --> 01:08:50.921
[Cheers and applause]

01:08:50.923 --> 01:08:52.357
Hey.

01:08:52.390 --> 01:08:54.609
Well, that's that
taken care of.

01:08:54.644 --> 01:08:56.761
- You ready?
- Absolutely.

01:08:56.796 --> 01:09:00.031
And now, Tony award winner,
Daisy Parker

01:09:00.066 --> 01:09:02.067
performing <i>Reach for me</i>
from <i>Hit List.</i>

01:09:02.100 --> 01:09:04.653
Well, it looks like someone
forgot to tell the announcer.

01:09:04.703 --> 01:09:06.787
[Laughs]

01:09:06.822 --> 01:09:12.077
♪ [A cappella]
I'm high above the city ♪

01:09:12.111 --> 01:09:17.249
♪ I'm standing on the ledge

01:09:17.283 --> 01:09:22.220
♪ the view from here is pretty

01:09:22.255 --> 01:09:26.890
♪ and I'm step off the edge

01:09:26.926 --> 01:09:29.644
♪ and now I'm fallin', baby

01:09:29.679 --> 01:09:31.813
♪ through the sky
through the sky ♪

01:09:31.846 --> 01:09:36.134
♪ I'm fallin', baby,
through the sky ♪

01:09:36.152 --> 01:09:40.822
♪ it's my callin', baby,
don't you cry, don't you cry ♪

01:09:40.856 --> 01:09:44.158
♪ I'm fallin'
down through the sky ♪

01:09:44.193 --> 01:09:46.778
Both: ♪ toward the street
that I'm from ♪

01:09:46.812 --> 01:09:49.814
[Rhythmic clapping]

01:09:49.832 --> 01:09:54.419
♪ Oh, Broadway, here I come

01:09:54.453 --> 01:09:58.089
♪ Broadway, here I co-ome

01:09:58.124 --> 01:10:02.260
♪ the pressure, it increases

01:10:02.295 --> 01:10:06.664
♪ the closer that I get

01:10:06.682 --> 01:10:10.852
♪ I could almost
go to pieces ♪

01:10:10.886 --> 01:10:15.056
♪ but I'm not quite there yet

01:10:15.107 --> 01:10:18.310
♪ see, I've been bravin'
crazy weather ♪

01:10:18.344 --> 01:10:20.612
♪ ooh, ooh

01:10:20.646 --> 01:10:24.816
- ♪ drownin' out my cries
- ♪ ooh, ooh

01:10:24.850 --> 01:10:28.920
- ♪ I pull myself together
- ♪ ooh, ooh

01:10:28.954 --> 01:10:31.022
♪ I'm focused on the prize

01:10:31.040 --> 01:10:33.241
- ♪ I'm
- ♪ fallin', baby

01:10:33.292 --> 01:10:35.526
♪ through the sky
through the sky ♪

01:10:35.544 --> 01:10:39.464
♪ I'm fallin', baby,
through the sky ♪

01:10:39.498 --> 01:10:44.252
♪ it's my callin', baby,
don't you cry, don't you cry ♪

01:10:44.303 --> 01:10:47.538
♪ I'm falling
down through the sky ♪

01:10:47.556 --> 01:10:50.975
♪ and I refuse to go numb

01:10:51.010 --> 01:10:55.513
- ♪ oh, oh, oh
- ♪ oh, Broadway, here I come

01:10:55.547 --> 01:10:58.216
♪ ah, ah, ah

01:10:58.234 --> 01:11:02.237
- ♪ Broadway, here I come
- ♪ Broadway, here I come

01:11:02.271 --> 01:11:06.724
♪ Broadway, here I come

01:11:06.742 --> 01:11:12.614
- ♪ Broadway, here I co-ome
- ♪ oh, oh, oh

01:11:12.665 --> 01:11:14.449
[rhythmic clapping]

01:11:14.500 --> 01:11:20.505
[Cheers and applause]

01:11:34.553 --> 01:11:37.856
I love you too.

01:11:40.943 --> 01:11:44.479
Oh.

01:11:44.530 --> 01:11:47.982
After all that...

01:11:48.033 --> 01:11:50.985
It ends here, huh?

01:11:51.036 --> 01:11:53.872
I have a confession.

01:11:53.906 --> 01:11:56.774
Hey, guys, I wanted to offer
you both my congratulations

01:11:56.792 --> 01:11:58.159
before everyone got to you.

01:11:58.210 --> 01:11:59.494
I'm on the last flight
back to L.A.

01:11:59.545 --> 01:12:01.663
Thank you, Patrick.
That's very kind of you.

01:12:01.714 --> 01:12:04.999
Look, this might seem like
it's coming out of left field,

01:12:05.050 --> 01:12:08.503
but have you two ever considered
writing a movie?

01:12:08.554 --> 01:12:10.672
I got the rights
to this really great story

01:12:10.723 --> 01:12:12.841
that's just begging to be
a movie musical,

01:12:12.875 --> 01:12:14.959
and I can't find
the right team to write it.

01:12:14.977 --> 01:12:17.979
You are still a team,
aren't you?

01:12:18.013 --> 01:12:19.681
We are.

01:12:19.732 --> 01:12:22.016
Well, I'd love to talk
with you both about it.

01:12:22.067 --> 01:12:23.985
I'll have my assistant
set it up.

01:12:24.019 --> 01:12:26.187
And congratulations.

01:12:26.238 --> 01:12:28.606
I voted for you.

01:12:29.975 --> 01:12:30.975
[Chuckles]

01:12:30.976 --> 01:12:32.193
- Go after him.
- What?

01:12:32.244 --> 01:12:33.995
Go after him!
Go, now. Go.

01:12:34.029 --> 01:12:35.313
- I don't...
- Go, go get him.

01:12:35.331 --> 01:12:36.865
Patrick!

01:12:36.916 --> 01:12:38.983
Patrick,
wait up a sec.

01:12:39.001 --> 01:12:43.521
Um, I might be crazy right now,
egotistically emboldened

01:12:43.556 --> 01:12:46.374
by my recent
and well-deserved win...

01:12:46.408 --> 01:12:48.760
- [Laughs]
- But I couldn't let you go

01:12:48.794 --> 01:12:52.347
without asking, um...

01:12:52.381 --> 01:12:55.666
Any chance when you're back,
we could maybe...

01:12:55.684 --> 01:13:00.138
Grab a bite to eat,
outside of a meeting?

01:13:00.172 --> 01:13:02.840
Tom, I'm flattered,
but I'm not...

01:13:08.113 --> 01:13:10.665
Gay.

01:13:10.699 --> 01:13:12.116
Nope, yup.

01:13:12.151 --> 01:13:15.470
That's... that's how
all my straight friends kiss me.

01:13:15.504 --> 01:13:17.288
Coming up, awards
for best actress in a musical...

01:13:17.323 --> 01:13:18.623
Uh...

01:13:18.657 --> 01:13:20.358
- Great.
- And best musical.

01:13:20.376 --> 01:13:24.295
Mm hmm.

01:13:24.330 --> 01:13:28.483
Welcome three-time
Tony nominee, Marin Mazzie.

01:13:28.517 --> 01:13:30.001
Thank you.

01:13:30.035 --> 01:13:32.303
The nominees
for best performance

01:13:32.338 --> 01:13:35.974
by an actress in a leading role
in a musical are...

01:13:36.008 --> 01:13:40.512
Kate Baldwin for <i>Seesaw.</i>

01:13:40.546 --> 01:13:42.514
Karen Cartwright
for <i>Hit List.</i>

01:13:42.548 --> 01:13:43.731
[Cheering]

01:13:43.766 --> 01:13:45.600
- [Laughs]
- Whoo! Whoo!

01:13:45.651 --> 01:13:49.654
Sutton Foster for <i>Oliver!</i>

01:13:49.688 --> 01:13:53.858
Ivy Lynn for <i>Bombshell.</i>

01:13:53.892 --> 01:13:58.530
And Audra McDonald
for <i>House of flowers.</i>

01:13:58.564 --> 01:14:02.033
And the Tony award goes to...

01:14:07.413 --> 01:14:10.398
Ivy Lynn, <i>Bombshell</i>.
[Cheers and applause].

01:14:10.416 --> 01:14:13.401
[Awards music]

01:14:13.419 --> 01:14:15.036
♪

01:14:15.070 --> 01:14:17.956
- Go on, go on.
- Okay, okay.

01:14:18.007 --> 01:14:26.007
♪

01:14:34.710 --> 01:14:40.214
Wow, um, okay. I-I honestly
didn't think I would win.

01:14:40.249 --> 01:14:44.785
Um, Tom, Julia, Eileen,

01:14:44.803 --> 01:14:47.972
thank you so much
for the chance of a lifetime.

01:14:48.006 --> 01:14:52.459
Um, I'd like to thank
my mother, Leigh Conroy,

01:14:52.478 --> 01:14:57.565
the magnificent Leigh Conroy
for giving me the greatest gift,

01:14:57.599 --> 01:15:01.235
and that is a life
in the theater.

01:15:01.270 --> 01:15:03.905
I can only hope
that one day,

01:15:03.939 --> 01:15:06.974
I can give that gift
to my children.

01:15:06.992 --> 01:15:10.111
For me,
there is nothing more magical

01:15:10.145 --> 01:15:13.147
than that moment
right as the lights go down

01:15:13.182 --> 01:15:15.917
and the crowd
is waiting in silence

01:15:15.951 --> 01:15:18.786
with anticipation
for the show to begin.

01:15:18.821 --> 01:15:23.824
It's a moment full of hope
and full of possibilities.

01:15:23.842 --> 01:15:28.379
So I'd like to thank
the audience for coming,

01:15:28.413 --> 01:15:30.681
and for believing,
as I do,

01:15:30.716 --> 01:15:35.553
that there is nothing
more important or special

01:15:35.604 --> 01:15:38.890
as live theater.
Thank you so much.

01:15:38.941 --> 01:15:41.893
[Music swells]

01:15:41.944 --> 01:15:49.617
♪

01:15:57.659 --> 01:16:00.578
- Karen.
- Oh, Eileen.

01:16:00.629 --> 01:16:03.331
What are you doing out here?
Your category's up next.

01:16:03.365 --> 01:16:05.082
I wanted to talk to you.

01:16:05.133 --> 01:16:07.351
I know how you must be feeling
right now,

01:16:07.386 --> 01:16:11.872
but let me tell you, as somebody
who lost a great many times

01:16:11.890 --> 01:16:13.925
before I ever won,

01:16:13.976 --> 01:16:15.977
time's on your side.

01:16:16.011 --> 01:16:18.112
Don't lose heart.

01:16:18.146 --> 01:16:21.315
Ms. Rand, it's time.

01:16:21.350 --> 01:16:23.734
Thanks.

01:16:23.769 --> 01:16:26.821
Good luck.
Thanks.

01:16:26.855 --> 01:16:29.657
Here to present the award
for best musical,

01:16:29.691 --> 01:16:33.444
Rosie O'Donnell.
[Applause]

01:16:33.495 --> 01:16:36.397
And now, the award
we've all been waiting for,

01:16:36.415 --> 01:16:39.033
best musical.

01:16:39.067 --> 01:16:42.003
The nominees are
<i>Bombshell...</i>

01:16:42.037 --> 01:16:44.789
[Cheers and applause]

01:16:44.840 --> 01:16:48.175
<i>The gathering storm,</i>

01:16:48.210 --> 01:16:50.711
<i>Hit List,</i>

01:16:50.745 --> 01:16:53.080
<Iimitation of life.

01:16:53.098 --> 01:16:56.300
Let it be us.
Let it be us.

01:16:56.351 --> 01:17:00.354
And the Tony award
goes to...

01:17:02.257 --> 01:17:03.257
<i>Bombshell.</i>

01:17:03.258 --> 01:17:05.142
[Cheers and applause]

01:17:05.193 --> 01:17:08.145
[Triumphant music]

01:17:08.196 --> 01:17:14.201
♪

01:17:22.110 --> 01:17:24.712
Derek!

01:17:30.469 --> 01:17:32.053
Don't worry,
they'll get over it.

01:17:32.087 --> 01:17:33.471
All they need
is another show.

01:17:33.505 --> 01:17:35.056
I'm game if you are.

01:17:35.090 --> 01:17:37.425
[Cheers and applause]

01:17:37.459 --> 01:17:39.927
Come on, everyone.

01:17:39.961 --> 01:17:43.147
[Cheers and applause]

01:17:48.303 --> 01:17:52.273
Best musical,
best actress, best score.

01:17:52.307 --> 01:17:55.276
How does it feel?

01:17:55.310 --> 01:17:56.643
It spins.

01:17:56.662 --> 01:18:00.314
- Hey.
- Hey.

01:18:00.332 --> 01:18:03.834
- Do you want to go talk?
- Yeah.

01:18:06.988 --> 01:18:09.156
- Oh, there he is.
- Oh.

01:18:09.174 --> 01:18:11.926
- Congratulations.
- [Chuckles]

01:18:11.960 --> 01:18:14.845
This one means a lot to me.

01:18:14.880 --> 01:18:17.498
Sorry.
I'm kidding. [Laughs]

01:18:17.516 --> 01:18:19.967
It's fine, congrats.

01:18:20.001 --> 01:18:24.138
Hey, you want to come outside
with me for a second?

01:18:24.172 --> 01:18:27.174
Okay.

01:18:29.010 --> 01:18:30.644
Hey.

01:18:30.678 --> 01:18:32.446
Oh, of course.
Thank you.

01:18:34.682 --> 01:18:36.851
- [Sighs]
- What are you doing?

01:18:36.885 --> 01:18:40.454
Just... sit.
[Clears throat]

01:18:40.489 --> 01:18:43.207
What is this?
You're making me nervous.

01:18:43.241 --> 01:18:47.194
[Chuckles]

01:18:47.212 --> 01:18:51.732
I know that I have been shady
with my past,

01:18:51.767 --> 01:18:54.251
and I've only ever told you
anything when you've pushed

01:18:54.302 --> 01:18:57.221
and not even then.
[Chuckles]

01:18:57.255 --> 01:19:01.875
So... five years ago,

01:19:01.893 --> 01:19:06.881
I was at this party with a girl
that I hardly even knew,

01:19:06.915 --> 01:19:09.817
and I had some stuff
with me.

01:19:09.851 --> 01:19:16.557
We used it, and she...
Did too much.

01:19:16.575 --> 01:19:18.225
I don't think I want
to hear this right now.

01:19:18.243 --> 01:19:21.562
Karen, she was just
lying there, not moving,

01:19:21.580 --> 01:19:23.948
and instead of telling anyone,
I ran.

01:19:23.999 --> 01:19:26.567
I mean, I went off the grid,
I hid with Adam, Kyle,

01:19:26.585 --> 01:19:27.901
I eventually
changed my name.

01:19:27.919 --> 01:19:30.421
I've been looking
over my shoulder for so long,

01:19:30.455 --> 01:19:32.840
I couldn't even
see my future anymore.

01:19:32.874 --> 01:19:34.525
Why are you telling me this
right now?

01:19:34.559 --> 01:19:38.979
Because this has haunted me
every day...

01:19:39.014 --> 01:19:41.465
Until today.

01:19:41.500 --> 01:19:43.917
What did you do?

01:19:43.935 --> 01:19:45.469
I turned myself in.

01:19:45.504 --> 01:19:48.939
- Oh, God, Jimmy.
- Hey, hey, here's the thing.

01:19:48.990 --> 01:19:51.575
She's okay.
She's not dead, she didn't die.

01:19:51.610 --> 01:19:53.828
They told me she's fine.
[Laughs]

01:19:53.862 --> 01:19:55.529
So you're okay?

01:19:55.564 --> 01:19:59.183
Uh, distribution
of a controlled substance.

01:19:59.217 --> 01:20:00.835
Most likely
6 to 18 months,

01:20:00.869 --> 01:20:05.122
but... but the cops commended me
for doing the right thing.

01:20:05.157 --> 01:20:09.210
I posted bail
right before I came to you.

01:20:09.244 --> 01:20:13.464
But I gotta go back
tonight.

01:20:13.515 --> 01:20:16.750
Hey.

01:20:16.768 --> 01:20:20.471
I told you...

01:20:20.522 --> 01:20:23.858
I would do
whatever I had to

01:20:23.892 --> 01:20:28.362
to be the person
you saw in me,

01:20:28.396 --> 01:20:32.700
and I can be
that person now.

01:20:36.538 --> 01:20:39.490
[Party chatter
and jazzy brass music]

01:20:39.541 --> 01:20:42.993
♪

01:20:43.044 --> 01:20:44.245
Mr. Levin.

01:20:44.279 --> 01:20:45.463
- [Laughs]
- Oh, thank you.

01:20:45.497 --> 01:20:46.914
- What's going on?
- Well, we were still

01:20:46.948 --> 01:20:47.965
in the back
when they did our song.

01:20:47.999 --> 01:20:51.618
- I didn't get to see it.
- Oh. Okay, oh.

01:20:51.636 --> 01:20:54.621
<i>[Big finish</i> playing]

01:20:54.639 --> 01:20:55.639
♪

01:20:55.640 --> 01:20:59.727
- Hi, Karen Cartwright.
- Hi, Ivy Lynn.

01:20:59.761 --> 01:21:01.896
Are you ready to give
the people what they want?

01:21:01.930 --> 01:21:02.930
Always.

01:21:02.931 --> 01:21:04.715
♪

01:21:04.749 --> 01:21:07.801
